1
00:00:28,266 --> 00:00:32,223
<i>The Tesseract has awakened.</i>

2
00:00:33,062 --> 00:00:38,021
<i>It is on a little world, a human world.</i>

3
00:00:38,736 --> 00:00:42,069
<i>They would wield its power,</i>

4
00:00:42,448 --> 00:00:48,118
<i>but our ally knows its</i>
<i>workings as they never will.</i>

5
00:00:49,663 --> 00:00:52,748
<i>He is ready to lead</i>

6
00:00:52,958 --> 00:00:58,379
<i>and our force, our Chitauri, will follow.</i>

7
00:01:00,008 --> 00:01:02,380
<i>A world will be his.</i>

8
00:01:02,594 --> 00:01:05,714
<i>The universe, yours.</i>

9
00:01:05,931 --> 00:01:11,803
<i>And the humans,</i>
<i>what can they do but burn?</i>

10
00:01:26,035 --> 00:01:27,114
<i>All personnel,</i>

11
00:01:27,286 --> 00:01:29,575
<i>the evacuation order</i>
<i>has been confirmed.</i>

12
00:02:01,489 --> 00:02:02,948
How bad is it?

13
00:02:03,158 --> 00:02:06,443
That's the problem, sir. We don't know.

14
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:12,957
Dr Selvig read an energy surge
from the Tesseract four hours ago.

15
00:02:13,084 --> 00:02:14,958
NASA didn't authorise Selvig
to go to test phase.

16
00:02:15,170 --> 00:02:17,328
He wasn't testing it.
He wasn't even in the room.

17
00:02:17,547 --> 00:02:18,543
Spontaneous event.

18
00:02:18,715 --> 00:02:19,830
It just turned itself on?

19
00:02:20,051 --> 00:02:21,082
Where are the energy levels now?

20
00:02:21,302 --> 00:02:23,460
Climbing. When Selvig couldn't
shut it down, we ordered evac.

21
00:02:23,679 --> 00:02:24,877
How long to get everyone out?

22
00:02:25,097 --> 00:02:26,426
Campus should be clear
in the next half-hour.

23
00:02:26,641 --> 00:02:27,886
Do better.

24
00:02:28,851 --> 00:02:30,808
Sir, evacuation may be futile.

25
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:32,395
We should tell them
to go back to sleep?

26
00:02:32,605 --> 00:02:34,811
If we can't control
the Tesseract's energy,

27
00:02:35,024 --> 00:02:37,349
there may not be
a minimum safe distance.

28
00:02:37,485 --> 00:02:38,516
I need you to make sure

29
00:02:38,653 --> 00:02:40,314
the Phase 2 prototypes
are shipped out.

30
00:02:40,489 --> 00:02:42,528
Sir, is that really a priority right now?

31
00:02:42,741 --> 00:02:44,449
Until such time as the world ends,

32
00:02:44,576 --> 00:02:46,616
we will act as though
it intends to spin on.

33
00:02:47,579 --> 00:02:48,955
Clear out the tech below.

34
00:02:49,164 --> 00:02:51,655
Every piece of Phase 2
on a truck and gone.

35
00:02:51,875 --> 00:02:52,954
Yes, sir.

36
00:02:53,377 --> 00:02:54,539
With me.

37
00:02:57,631 --> 00:02:58,627
Talk to me, Doctor.

38
00:03:00,425 --> 00:03:01,802
Director.

39
00:03:02,011 --> 00:03:03,671
Is there anything we know for certain?

40
00:03:03,888 --> 00:03:06,130
The Tesseract is misbehaving.

41
00:03:06,349 --> 00:03:09,136
- Is that supposed to be funny?
- No, it's not funny at all.

42
00:03:09,352 --> 00:03:12,851
The Tesseract is not only
active, she's behaving.

43
00:03:13,064 --> 00:03:14,060
I assume you pulled the plug.

44
00:03:14,274 --> 00:03:15,982
She's an energy source.

45
00:03:16,192 --> 00:03:19,229
We turn off the power,
she turns it back on.

46
00:03:19,445 --> 00:03:20,525
If she reaches peak level...

47
00:03:20,738 --> 00:03:24,155
We prepared for this, Doctor.
Harnessing energy from space.

48
00:03:24,368 --> 00:03:25,743
But we don't have the harness.

49
00:03:25,870 --> 00:03:27,150
My calculations are far from complete.

50
00:03:27,705 --> 00:03:30,243
And she's throwing off
interference, radiation.

51
00:03:30,458 --> 00:03:32,165
Nothing harmful,
low levels of gamma radiation.

52
00:03:33,085 --> 00:03:34,912
That can be harmful.

53
00:03:35,129 --> 00:03:36,540
Where's Agent Barton?

54
00:03:36,714 --> 00:03:38,422
The Hawk?

55
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:41,340
Up in his nest, as usual.

56
00:03:42,804 --> 00:03:44,596
<i>Agent Barton, report.</i>

57
00:03:45,474 --> 00:03:46,636
<i>I gave you this detail</i>

58
00:03:46,767 --> 00:03:48,344
<i>so you could keep
a close eye on things.</i>

59
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,935
Well, I see better from a distance.

60
00:03:50,145 --> 00:03:52,102
Have you seen anything
that might set this thing off?

61
00:03:52,564 --> 00:03:54,687
Doctor, it's spiking again.

62
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,275
No one's come or gone.

63
00:03:56,485 --> 00:03:58,109
And Selvig's clean.

64
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:00,609
No contacts, no IMs.

65
00:04:01,114 --> 00:04:02,907
If there was any tampering,
sir, it wasn't at this end.

66
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:06,203
"At this end"?

67
00:04:06,412 --> 00:04:10,244
Yeah, the Cube is a doorway to
the other end of space, right?

68
00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:13,365
Doors open from both sides.

69
00:04:14,128 --> 00:04:15,457
Not yet.

70
00:05:23,368 --> 00:05:26,488
Sir, please put down the spear.

71
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:06,992
You have heart.

72
00:06:37,571 --> 00:06:39,065
Please don't.

73
00:06:40,866 --> 00:06:42,064
I still need that.

74
00:06:42,284 --> 00:06:43,744
This doesn't have to get any messier.

75
00:06:43,953 --> 00:06:45,151
Of course it does.

76
00:06:45,371 --> 00:06:47,245
I've come too far for anything else.

77
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:51,996
I am Loki, of Asgard

78
00:06:52,712 --> 00:06:55,084
and I am burdened with
glorious purpose.

79
00:06:55,298 --> 00:06:56,709
Loki,

80
00:06:57,216 --> 00:06:58,497
brother of Thor.

81
00:06:58,718 --> 00:07:01,173
We have no quarrel with your people.

82
00:07:01,387 --> 00:07:04,342
An ant has no quarrel with a boot.

83
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:06,593
Are you planning to step on us?

84
00:07:06,935 --> 00:07:10,020
I come with glad tidings

85
00:07:11,273 --> 00:07:13,182
of a world made free.

86
00:07:13,567 --> 00:07:14,563
Free from what?

87
00:07:14,777 --> 00:07:16,105
Freedom.

88
00:07:16,654 --> 00:07:19,275
Freedom is life's great lie.

89
00:07:19,490 --> 00:07:22,906
Once you accept that, in your heart,

90
00:07:27,415 --> 00:07:29,289
you will know peace.

91
00:07:29,584 --> 00:07:32,040
Yeah, you say "peace,"

92
00:07:32,253 --> 00:07:34,080
I kind of think you mean the other thing.

93
00:07:34,297 --> 00:07:36,788
Sir, Director Fury is stalling.

94
00:07:37,008 --> 00:07:38,337
This place is about to blow

95
00:07:38,468 --> 00:07:40,176
and drop a hundred feet of rock on us.

96
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:42,711
He means to bury us.

97
00:07:42,931 --> 00:07:44,045
Like the pharaohs of old.

98
00:07:44,266 --> 00:07:46,224
He's right. The portal
is collapsing in on itself.

99
00:07:46,435 --> 00:07:48,642
We've got maybe two minutes
before this goes critical.

100
00:07:49,021 --> 00:07:50,017
Well, then.

101
00:08:05,789 --> 00:08:06,868
I need these vehicles.

102
00:08:10,961 --> 00:08:13,084
- Who's that?
- They didn't tell me.

103
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,545
<i>Hill!</i>

104
00:08:17,968 --> 00:08:19,248
Do you copy?

105
00:08:19,970 --> 00:08:21,298
<i>Barton has turned.</i>

106
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:37,196
They have the Tesseract!
Shut them down!

107
00:09:13,610 --> 00:09:15,816
Okay, let's go. No, leave it. Go!

108
00:09:32,296 --> 00:09:34,419
We're clear upstairs, sir.
You need to go.

109
00:11:06,395 --> 00:11:07,724
<i>Director?</i>

110
00:11:08,064 --> 00:11:09,558
Director Fury, do you copy?

111
00:11:09,774 --> 00:11:12,063
The Tesseract is with a hostile force.

112
00:11:12,318 --> 00:11:14,726
I have men down. Hill?

113
00:11:15,071 --> 00:11:16,945
A lot of men still under.

114
00:11:17,157 --> 00:11:18,864
I don't know how many survivors.

115
00:11:19,075 --> 00:11:20,238
<i>Sound a general call.</i>

116
00:11:20,451 --> 00:11:22,159
I want every living soul
not working rescue

117
00:11:22,287 --> 00:11:23,282
looking for that briefcase.

118
00:11:23,496 --> 00:11:24,527
Roger that.

119
00:11:24,747 --> 00:11:28,034
Coulson, get back to base.
This is a Level Seven.

120
00:11:29,128 --> 00:11:30,705
<i>As of right now,</i>

121
00:11:30,921 --> 00:11:32,380
we are at war.

122
00:11:34,091 --> 00:11:35,372
What do we do?

123
00:12:12,256 --> 00:12:15,957
This is not how I wanted this evening
to go.

124
00:12:16,094 --> 00:12:17,718
I know how you wanted this evening
to go.

125
00:12:17,929 --> 00:12:19,008
Believe me

126
00:12:19,138 --> 00:12:20,170
this is better.

127
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:23,014
Who are you working for?

128
00:12:23,393 --> 00:12:24,970
Lermentov, yes?

129
00:12:26,938 --> 00:12:28,397
Does he think

130
00:12:29,024 --> 00:12:30,816
we have to go through him

131
00:12:31,110 --> 00:12:32,568
to move our cargo?

132
00:12:33,821 --> 00:12:38,364
I thought General Solohob
is in charge of the export business.

133
00:12:38,701 --> 00:12:40,658
Solohob

134
00:12:40,869 --> 00:12:42,909
a bagman, a front.

135
00:12:45,374 --> 00:12:49,538
Your outdated information betrays you.

136
00:12:51,131 --> 00:12:53,882
The famous Black Widow

137
00:12:55,552 --> 00:12:59,929
and she turns out to be
simply another pretty face.

138
00:13:00,807 --> 00:13:03,974
You really think I'm pretty?

139
00:13:06,521 --> 00:13:08,763
Tell Lermentov we don't need him

140
00:13:09,065 --> 00:13:12,649
to move the tanks.

141
00:13:13,613 --> 00:13:16,234
Tell him he is out.

142
00:13:16,657 --> 00:13:18,282
Well...

143
00:13:21,162 --> 00:13:22,905
...you may have to write it down.

144
00:13:31,882 --> 00:13:33,341
It's for her.

145
00:13:36,803 --> 00:13:38,084
You listen carefully

146
00:13:38,222 --> 00:13:40,795
<i>You're at 1- 14
Silensky Plaza, 3rd floor.</i>

147
00:13:41,058 --> 00:13:43,181
<i>We have an F-22
exactly eight miles out.</i>

148
00:13:44,061 --> 00:13:46,018
<i>Put the woman on the phone,
or I will blow up the block</i>

149
00:13:46,230 --> 00:13:48,269
<i>before you can make the lobby.</i>

150
00:13:54,739 --> 00:13:56,862
<i>- We need you to come in.
- Are you kidding? I'm working.</i>

151
00:13:57,075 --> 00:13:58,355
<i>This takes precedence.</i>

152
00:13:58,576 --> 00:14:00,201
I'm in the middle of an interrogation.

153
00:14:00,370 --> 00:14:02,161
This moron is giving me everything.

154
00:14:02,580 --> 00:14:05,202
I don't give everything.

155
00:14:06,626 --> 00:14:08,001
Look, you can't pull me
out of this right now.

156
00:14:08,127 --> 00:14:09,123
<i>Natasha...</i>

157
00:14:10,714 --> 00:14:12,209
Barton's been compromised.

158
00:14:15,428 --> 00:14:17,254
Let me put you on hold.

159
00:14:59,015 --> 00:15:00,011
Where is Barton now?

160
00:15:00,183 --> 00:15:01,677
<i>- We don't know.
- But he's alive?</i>

161
00:15:01,893 --> 00:15:04,680
We think so. I'll brief you on
everything when you get back.

162
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:06,977
But first, we need you to
talk to the big guy.

163
00:15:07,190 --> 00:15:10,274
Coulson, you know that Stark trusts me
about as far as he can throw me.

164
00:15:10,485 --> 00:15:13,985
I've got Stark. You get the big guy.

165
00:15:38,723 --> 00:15:39,719
Who are you?

166
00:15:40,183 --> 00:15:41,262
Get out!

167
00:15:41,393 --> 00:15:43,884
There is sickness here!

168
00:15:44,020 --> 00:15:45,016
You're a doctor.

169
00:15:46,731 --> 00:15:48,012
My father's not waking up!

170
00:15:48,149 --> 00:15:49,976
He has a fever and he's moaning

171
00:15:50,110 --> 00:15:51,189
but his eyes won't open.

172
00:15:51,319 --> 00:15:52,316
Slow down.

173
00:15:53,864 --> 00:15:54,944
My father...

174
00:15:57,326 --> 00:15:58,322
Like them?

175
00:16:02,331 --> 00:16:03,576
Please.

176
00:16:30,777 --> 00:16:33,067
You should've got paid
up front, Banner.

177
00:16:33,281 --> 00:16:34,561
You know, for a man

178
00:16:34,699 --> 00:16:35,980
who's supposed to be avoiding stress

179
00:16:36,201 --> 00:16:39,451
you picked a hell of a place to settle.

180
00:16:41,206 --> 00:16:43,412
Avoiding stress isn't the secret.

181
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:46,116
Then what is it? Yoga?

182
00:16:47,295 --> 00:16:50,462
You brought me to the edge of
the city. Smart.

183
00:16:51,049 --> 00:16:55,094
I assume the whole place
is surrounded.

184
00:16:55,554 --> 00:16:56,930
Just you and me.

185
00:16:58,182 --> 00:17:00,221
And your actress buddy?

186
00:17:00,434 --> 00:17:02,391
Is she a spy, too?
They start that young?

187
00:17:02,812 --> 00:17:04,057
I did.

188
00:17:04,271 --> 00:17:05,303
Who are you?

189
00:17:05,523 --> 00:17:06,637
Natasha Romanoff.

190
00:17:09,985 --> 00:17:11,314
Are you here to kill me, Ms Romanoff?

191
00:17:11,529 --> 00:17:14,234
Because that's not going to
work out for everyone.

192
00:17:14,449 --> 00:17:16,905
No, of course not. I'm here
on behalf of S.H.I.E.L.D.

193
00:17:18,662 --> 00:17:20,156
S.H.I.E.L.D.

194
00:17:21,957 --> 00:17:22,953
How did they find me?

195
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:24,749
We never lost you, Doctor.

196
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:25,956
We've kept our distance.

197
00:17:26,169 --> 00:17:27,961
Even helped keep some other
interested parties

198
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:29,161
off your scent.

199
00:17:29,673 --> 00:17:30,669
Why?

200
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:33,172
Nick Fury seems to trust you.

201
00:17:33,386 --> 00:17:35,010
But now we need you to come in.

202
00:17:35,972 --> 00:17:37,846
What if I say no?

203
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:40,180
I'll persuade you.

204
00:17:42,311 --> 00:17:46,641
And what if the other guy says no?

205
00:17:47,358 --> 00:17:48,983
You've been more than a year
without an incident.

206
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:51,767
I don't think you want to
break that streak.

207
00:17:53,991 --> 00:17:56,612
Well, I don't every time get what I want.

208
00:17:57,661 --> 00:17:59,868
Doctor, we're facing a potential
global catastrophe.

209
00:18:00,706 --> 00:18:03,826
Well, those I actively try to avoid.

210
00:18:04,168 --> 00:18:06,207
This

211
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:08,792
is the Tesseract.

212
00:18:09,006 --> 00:18:11,793
It has the potential energy
to wipe out the planet.

213
00:18:14,638 --> 00:18:16,796
What does Fury want me to do,
swallow it?

214
00:18:17,015 --> 00:18:19,471
He wants you to find it. It's been taken.

215
00:18:20,310 --> 00:18:24,473
It emits a gamma signature
that's too weak for us to trace.

216
00:18:24,689 --> 00:18:27,607
There's no one that knows
gamma radiation like you do.

217
00:18:27,817 --> 00:18:30,605
If there was, that's where I'd be.

218
00:18:31,196 --> 00:18:33,354
So, Fury isn't after the monster?

219
00:18:33,573 --> 00:18:34,819
Not that he's told me.

220
00:18:35,034 --> 00:18:37,192
And he tells you everything?

221
00:18:37,870 --> 00:18:39,245
Talk to Fury. He needs you on this.

222
00:18:39,372 --> 00:18:40,403
He needs me in a cage?

223
00:18:40,539 --> 00:18:41,535
No one's going to put you in a...

224
00:18:41,707 --> 00:18:42,703
Stop lying to me!

225
00:18:46,921 --> 00:18:49,542
I'm sorry. That was mean.

226
00:18:50,508 --> 00:18:52,666
I just wanted to see what you'd do.

227
00:18:53,886 --> 00:18:56,841
Why don't we do this the easy way

228
00:18:57,057 --> 00:18:58,302
where you don't use that

229
00:18:58,517 --> 00:19:02,431
and the other guy
doesn't make a mess.

230
00:19:03,230 --> 00:19:04,510
Okay?

231
00:19:05,524 --> 00:19:06,852
Natasha?

232
00:19:12,531 --> 00:19:13,562
Stand down.

233
00:19:14,534 --> 00:19:16,076
<i>We're good here.</i>

234
00:19:17,912 --> 00:19:19,454
"Just you and me."

235
00:19:21,624 --> 00:19:24,198
<i>This is out of line, Director.</i>

236
00:19:24,419 --> 00:19:26,826
<i>You're dealing
with forces you can't control.</i>

237
00:19:27,255 --> 00:19:30,706
You ever been in a war,
Councilman? In a firefight?

238
00:19:30,925 --> 00:19:33,712
Did you feel
an overabundance of control?

239
00:19:33,928 --> 00:19:37,298
<i>You're saying that this Asgard
is declaring war on our planet?</i>

240
00:19:37,433 --> 00:19:40,054
Not Asgard. Loki.

241
00:19:40,269 --> 00:19:43,056
<i>He can't be working alone.
What about the other one?</i>

242
00:19:43,189 --> 00:19:44,220
<i>His brother.</i>

243
00:19:44,356 --> 00:19:46,396
Our intelligence says
Thor is not a hostile

244
00:19:46,609 --> 00:19:47,604
but he's worlds away.

245
00:19:47,777 --> 00:19:49,568
We can't depend on him to help, either.

246
00:19:49,695 --> 00:19:50,691
It's up to us.

247
00:19:50,821 --> 00:19:53,443
<i>Which is why you
should be focusing on Phase 2.</i>

248
00:19:53,616 --> 00:19:54,896
<i>It was designed for exactly this...</i>

249
00:19:55,118 --> 00:19:58,285
Phase 2 isn't ready. Our enemy is.

250
00:19:58,538 --> 00:20:00,080
We need a response team.

251
00:20:00,290 --> 00:20:02,579
<i>The Avengers Initiative was shut down.</i>

252
00:20:02,793 --> 00:20:04,584
This isn't about the Avengers.

253
00:20:04,795 --> 00:20:05,909
<i>We've seen the list.</i>

254
00:20:06,129 --> 00:20:08,336
<i>You're running the world's greatest
covert security network</i>

255
00:20:08,465 --> 00:20:10,089
<i>and you're going to leave
the fate of the human race</i>

256
00:20:10,258 --> 00:20:11,503
<i>to a handful of freaks.</i>

257
00:20:11,635 --> 00:20:13,544
I'm not leaving anything to anyone.

258
00:20:13,762 --> 00:20:15,969
We need a response team.

259
00:20:16,224 --> 00:20:18,929
These people may be isolated,
unbalanced even

260
00:20:19,143 --> 00:20:23,307
but I believe with the right push
they can be exactly what we need.

261
00:20:23,606 --> 00:20:24,887
<i>You believe?</i>

262
00:20:25,108 --> 00:20:28,690
<i>War isn't won by sentiment, Director.</i>

263
00:20:29,404 --> 00:20:32,737
No, it's won by soldiers.

264
00:20:52,386 --> 00:20:54,177
<i>There's not enough time.</i>

265
00:20:54,388 --> 00:20:55,930
<i>I got to put her in the water!</i>

266
00:21:01,313 --> 00:21:02,344
<i>You won't be alone.</i>

267
00:21:02,939 --> 00:21:04,433
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

268
00:21:04,899 --> 00:21:06,062
<i>This guy is still alive!</i>

269
00:21:30,843 --> 00:21:32,587
Trouble sleeping?

270
00:21:33,930 --> 00:21:36,600
I slept for 70 years, sir.
I think I've had my fill.

271
00:21:38,143 --> 00:21:42,057
Then you should be out,
celebrating, seeing the world.

272
00:21:47,903 --> 00:21:50,738
When I went under,
the world was at war.

273
00:21:50,948 --> 00:21:52,774
I wake up, they say we won.

274
00:21:53,492 --> 00:21:55,034
They didn't say what we lost.

275
00:21:55,619 --> 00:21:57,945
We've made some mistakes
along the way.

276
00:21:58,373 --> 00:22:00,033
Some, very recently.

277
00:22:01,584 --> 00:22:02,782
Are you here with a mission, sir?

278
00:22:02,919 --> 00:22:03,915
I am.

279
00:22:04,045 --> 00:22:05,705
Trying to get me back in the world?

280
00:22:06,214 --> 00:22:07,874
Trying to save it.

281
00:22:12,554 --> 00:22:14,546
HYDRA's secret weapon.

282
00:22:14,764 --> 00:22:16,840
Howard Stark fished that
out of the ocean

283
00:22:16,975 --> 00:22:18,090
when he was looking for you.

284
00:22:18,644 --> 00:22:20,304
He thought what we think.

285
00:22:20,563 --> 00:22:24,691
The Tesseract could be the key
to unlimited sustainable energy.

286
00:22:25,151 --> 00:22:28,983
That's something
the world sorely needs.

287
00:22:30,489 --> 00:22:31,652
Who took it from you?

288
00:22:31,866 --> 00:22:33,276
He's called Loki.

289
00:22:33,492 --> 00:22:36,114
He's not from around here.

290
00:22:36,579 --> 00:22:38,656
There's a lot we'll have to
bring you up to speed on

291
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:39,988
if you're in.

292
00:22:40,917 --> 00:22:42,957
The world has gotten even stranger

293
00:22:43,086 --> 00:22:44,165
than you already know.

294
00:22:44,671 --> 00:22:47,245
At this point, I doubt
anything would surprise me.

295
00:22:47,883 --> 00:22:49,543
Ten bucks says you're wrong.

296
00:22:51,303 --> 00:22:52,678
There's a debriefing packet

297
00:22:52,804 --> 00:22:55,176
waiting for you back at your apartment.

298
00:22:57,559 --> 00:22:59,469
Is there anything you can
tell us about the Tesseract

299
00:22:59,604 --> 00:23:00,802
that we ought to know now?

300
00:23:01,105 --> 00:23:03,394
You should have left it in the ocean.

301
00:23:36,141 --> 00:23:39,013
<i>Good to go on this end.
The rest is up to you.</i>

302
00:23:39,229 --> 00:23:40,557
<i>You disconnected
the transmission lines?</i>

303
00:23:40,689 --> 00:23:41,684
<i>Are we off the grid?</i>

304
00:23:41,815 --> 00:23:43,973
Stark Tower is about to become
a beacon

305
00:23:44,150 --> 00:23:45,609
of self-sustaining clean energy.

306
00:23:45,735 --> 00:23:47,775
<i>Well, assuming
the arc reactor takes over</i>

307
00:23:47,904 --> 00:23:49,102
<i>and it actually works.</i>

308
00:23:49,489 --> 00:23:50,770
<i>I assume.</i>

309
00:23:51,283 --> 00:23:52,278
Light her up.

310
00:23:57,831 --> 00:23:58,828
<i>How does it look?</i>

311
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:01,669
Like Christmas, but with more me.

312
00:24:01,877 --> 00:24:03,621
<i>We've got to go wider on
the public awareness campaign.</i>

313
00:24:03,838 --> 00:24:04,869
<i>You need to do some press.</i>

314
00:24:05,506 --> 00:24:06,502
<i>I'm in DC tomorrow,</i>

315
00:24:06,674 --> 00:24:08,168
<i>I'm working on the zoning
for the next three buildings.</i>

316
00:24:08,342 --> 00:24:10,549
<i>Pepper, you're killing me.
The moment, remember?</i>

317
00:24:10,761 --> 00:24:11,793
<i>Enjoy the moment.</i>

318
00:24:12,013 --> 00:24:13,175
<i>Get in here and I will.</i>

319
00:24:16,517 --> 00:24:19,436
<i>Sir, Agent Coulson of
S.H.I.E.L.D. is on the line.</i>

320
00:24:20,022 --> 00:24:21,017
<i>I'm not in.</i>

321
00:24:21,690 --> 00:24:22,970
I'm actually out.

322
00:24:30,199 --> 00:24:32,820
<i>Sir, I'm afraid he's insisting.</i>

323
00:24:33,035 --> 00:24:35,786
Grow a spine, Jarvis. I got a date.

324
00:24:40,335 --> 00:24:43,289
Levels are holding steady, I think.

325
00:24:43,505 --> 00:24:45,663
Of course they are.
I was directly involved.

326
00:24:45,882 --> 00:24:47,045
Which brings me to my next question.

327
00:24:47,217 --> 00:24:49,174
How does it feel to be a genius?

328
00:24:49,385 --> 00:24:51,627
Well, I really wouldn't know,
now would I?

329
00:24:51,846 --> 00:24:56,342
What do you mean?
All this came from you.

330
00:24:56,559 --> 00:25:00,179
No, all this came from that.

331
00:25:00,397 --> 00:25:02,686
Give yourself some credit. Please.

332
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:04,691
Stark Tower is your baby.

333
00:25:04,902 --> 00:25:07,274
Give yourself 12% of the credit.

334
00:25:07,738 --> 00:25:08,853
12%?

335
00:25:08,989 --> 00:25:10,104
An argument can be made for 15.

336
00:25:10,241 --> 00:25:11,818
12%? My baby?

337
00:25:12,034 --> 00:25:13,612
Well, I did do all the heavy lifting.

338
00:25:13,744 --> 00:25:15,618
Literally, I lifted the heavy things.

339
00:25:15,871 --> 00:25:18,113
And, sorry, but the security snafu?

340
00:25:18,249 --> 00:25:19,707
That was on you.

341
00:25:19,876 --> 00:25:21,952
- My private elevator...
- You mean our elevator?

342
00:25:22,170 --> 00:25:24,840
...it was teeming with sweaty workmen.

343
00:25:25,048 --> 00:25:27,373
I'm going to pay for that
comment about percentages

344
00:25:27,592 --> 00:25:29,550
in some subtle way later, aren't I?

345
00:25:30,011 --> 00:25:31,210
It's not going to be that subtle.

346
00:25:31,430 --> 00:25:32,710
I'll tell you what.

347
00:25:32,931 --> 00:25:35,387
The next building is gonna
say "Potts" on the tower.

348
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:36,976
On the lease.

349
00:25:37,894 --> 00:25:40,017
Call your mom. Can you bunk over?

350
00:25:40,231 --> 00:25:41,476
<i>Sir, the telephone.</i>

351
00:25:41,691 --> 00:25:44,063
<i>I'm afraid my protocols
are being overridden.</i>

352
00:25:44,277 --> 00:25:46,234
<i>Mr Stark, we need to talk.</i>

353
00:25:46,529 --> 00:25:48,854
You have reached the life
model decoy of Tony Stark.

354
00:25:49,115 --> 00:25:51,072
<i>- Please leave a message.
- This is urgent.</i>

355
00:25:51,284 --> 00:25:53,075
Then leave it urgently.

356
00:25:54,620 --> 00:25:55,735
Security breach. It's on you.

357
00:25:55,955 --> 00:25:58,660
- Mr Stark.
- Phil! Come in.

358
00:25:58,833 --> 00:25:59,829
"Phil"?

359
00:25:59,959 --> 00:26:00,991
I can't stay.

360
00:26:01,211 --> 00:26:02,409
His first name is "Agent."

361
00:26:02,629 --> 00:26:04,254
Come on in. We're celebrating.

362
00:26:04,465 --> 00:26:06,256
Which is why he can't stay.

363
00:26:06,467 --> 00:26:08,424
We need you to look this over
as soon as possible.

364
00:26:08,636 --> 00:26:09,667
I don't like being handed things.

365
00:26:09,887 --> 00:26:11,346
That's fine, because
I love to be handed things.

366
00:26:11,555 --> 00:26:12,884
So, let's trade.

367
00:26:14,266 --> 00:26:15,760
Thank you.

368
00:26:16,977 --> 00:26:19,184
Official consulting hours
are between 8 and 5

369
00:26:19,313 --> 00:26:20,309
every other Thursday.

370
00:26:20,481 --> 00:26:21,478
This isn't a consultation.

371
00:26:21,608 --> 00:26:22,853
Is this about the Avengers?

372
00:26:23,276 --> 00:26:25,103
Which I know nothing about.

373
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:27,858
The Avengers Initiative
was scrapped, I thought.

374
00:26:28,073 --> 00:26:29,448
And I didn't even qualify.

375
00:26:29,658 --> 00:26:30,653
I didn't know that either.

376
00:26:30,825 --> 00:26:33,696
Apparently I'm volatile, self-obsessed,

377
00:26:33,828 --> 00:26:35,073
don't play well with others.

378
00:26:35,372 --> 00:26:36,367
That I did know.

379
00:26:36,498 --> 00:26:38,122
This isn't about personality
profiles any more.

380
00:26:38,291 --> 00:26:40,616
Whatever. Ms Potts, got a second?

381
00:26:40,835 --> 00:26:41,832
Half a mo.

382
00:26:47,134 --> 00:26:49,460
You know, I thought we were
having a moment.

383
00:26:49,679 --> 00:26:51,256
I was having 12% of a moment.

384
00:26:52,473 --> 00:26:54,929
This seems serious.
Phil's pretty shaken.

385
00:26:55,142 --> 00:26:57,100
How would you know if it's...
Why is he "Phil"?

386
00:26:57,311 --> 00:26:59,055
What is all this?

387
00:26:59,272 --> 00:27:00,814
This is

388
00:27:01,525 --> 00:27:02,521
this.

389
00:27:09,867 --> 00:27:11,242
I'm going to take the jet to DC tonight.

390
00:27:11,368 --> 00:27:12,399
Tomorrow.

391
00:27:12,536 --> 00:27:14,825
You have homework.
You have a lot of homework.

392
00:27:15,038 --> 00:27:16,746
Well, what if I didn't?

393
00:27:17,374 --> 00:27:18,749
- If you didn't?
- Yeah.

394
00:27:18,959 --> 00:27:21,117
You mean when you've finished?

395
00:27:22,213 --> 00:27:25,499
Well, then...

396
00:27:30,722 --> 00:27:32,002
Square deal. Fly safe.

397
00:27:36,227 --> 00:27:37,342
Work hard.

398
00:27:40,231 --> 00:27:41,976
So, any chance
you're driving by LaGuardia?

399
00:27:42,193 --> 00:27:44,944
- I can drop you.
- Fantastic.

400
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:46,066
I want to hear

401
00:27:46,197 --> 00:27:47,857
about the cellist. Is that still a thing?

402
00:27:48,073 --> 00:27:49,188
She moved back to Portland.

403
00:27:49,408 --> 00:27:52,528
What? Boo!

404
00:28:00,586 --> 00:28:02,995
We're about 40 minutes
out from home base, sir.

405
00:28:06,718 --> 00:28:10,383
So, this Dr Banner was trying
to replicate the serum they used on me?

406
00:28:10,597 --> 00:28:12,139
A lot of people were.

407
00:28:12,349 --> 00:28:13,973
You were the world's first superhero.

408
00:28:14,684 --> 00:28:17,389
Banner thought gamma radiation
might hold the key to unlocking

409
00:28:17,562 --> 00:28:18,891
Erskine's original formula.

410
00:28:19,940 --> 00:28:21,315
Didn't really go his way, did it?

411
00:28:21,733 --> 00:28:23,193
Not so much.

412
00:28:23,403 --> 00:28:26,238
When he's not that thing, though,
the guy's like a Stephen Hawking.

413
00:28:28,282 --> 00:28:30,820
He's like a smart person.

414
00:28:32,954 --> 00:28:34,068
I gotta say,

415
00:28:34,414 --> 00:28:36,821
it's an honour to meet you officially.

416
00:28:37,583 --> 00:28:39,078
I've sort of met you. I mean,

417
00:28:39,252 --> 00:28:41,043
I watched you while you were sleeping.

418
00:28:42,881 --> 00:28:45,088
I mean, I was present

419
00:28:45,301 --> 00:28:48,586
while you were
unconscious from the ice.

420
00:28:48,804 --> 00:28:51,093
You know, it's really just a huge honour

421
00:28:51,223 --> 00:28:53,180
to have you on board this...

422
00:28:53,559 --> 00:28:55,433
I hope I'm the man for the job.

423
00:28:55,644 --> 00:28:58,515
Oh, you are. Absolutely.

424
00:28:58,731 --> 00:29:01,601
We made some modifications
to the uniform.

425
00:29:01,817 --> 00:29:03,312
I had a little design input.

426
00:29:03,528 --> 00:29:04,773
The uniform?

427
00:29:04,988 --> 00:29:07,479
Aren't the stars and stripes a little

428
00:29:08,658 --> 00:29:09,987
old-fashioned?

429
00:29:10,827 --> 00:29:12,985
With everything that's happening

430
00:29:13,204 --> 00:29:14,829
and the things that are about
to come to light,

431
00:29:15,707 --> 00:29:19,158
people might just need
a little old-fashioned.

432
00:29:51,703 --> 00:29:54,657
The Chitauri grow restless.

433
00:29:54,873 --> 00:29:56,581
Let them gird themselves.

434
00:29:56,708 --> 00:29:58,500
I will lead them in the glorious battle.

435
00:29:58,710 --> 00:29:59,873
Battle?

436
00:30:00,712 --> 00:30:03,797
Against the meagre might of Earth?

437
00:30:04,008 --> 00:30:06,844
Glorious, not lengthy.

438
00:30:07,053 --> 00:30:10,837
If your force
is as formidable as you claim.

439
00:30:11,057 --> 00:30:13,548
You question us?

440
00:30:13,768 --> 00:30:15,891
You question him,

441
00:30:16,062 --> 00:30:18,518
he who put the sceptre in your hand?

442
00:30:18,731 --> 00:30:21,649
Who gave you ancient knowledge
and new purpose

443
00:30:21,860 --> 00:30:24,731
when you were cast out, defeated?

444
00:30:24,947 --> 00:30:26,821
I was a king!

445
00:30:27,032 --> 00:30:29,239
The rightful king of Asgard,

446
00:30:29,743 --> 00:30:30,739
betrayed.

447
00:30:31,412 --> 00:30:34,033
Your ambition is little

448
00:30:34,248 --> 00:30:37,000
and born of childish need.

449
00:30:37,209 --> 00:30:39,202
We look beyond the Earth

450
00:30:39,420 --> 00:30:42,374
to the greater worlds
the Tesseract will unveil.

451
00:30:42,840 --> 00:30:44,251
You don't have the Tesseract yet.

452
00:30:47,054 --> 00:30:48,049
I don't threaten.

453
00:30:49,598 --> 00:30:52,171
But until I open the doors,

454
00:30:52,392 --> 00:30:56,010
until your force is mine to command,

455
00:30:56,772 --> 00:30:58,563
you are but words.

456
00:30:58,774 --> 00:31:02,723
You will have your war, Asgardian.

457
00:31:04,529 --> 00:31:06,523
If you fail,

458
00:31:07,533 --> 00:31:11,911
if the Tesseract is kept from us,

459
00:31:12,121 --> 00:31:16,499
there will be no realm, no barren moon,

460
00:31:16,709 --> 00:31:19,995
no crevice where he cannot find you.

461
00:31:21,589 --> 00:31:24,341
You think you know pain?

462
00:31:24,550 --> 00:31:30,222
He will make you long
for something sweet as pain.

463
00:31:59,421 --> 00:32:00,452
Stow the captain's gear.

464
00:32:00,588 --> 00:32:01,584
Yes, sir.

465
00:32:03,133 --> 00:32:06,254
Agent Romanoff, Captain Rogers.

466
00:32:06,470 --> 00:32:07,751
- Ma'am.
- Hi.

467
00:32:07,930 --> 00:32:08,926
They need you on the bridge.

468
00:32:09,056 --> 00:32:10,551
They're starting the face-trace.

469
00:32:10,766 --> 00:32:11,846
See you there.

470
00:32:13,603 --> 00:32:17,731
It was quite the buzz around here,
finding you in the ice.

471
00:32:18,024 --> 00:32:20,597
I thought Coulson was gonna swoon.

472
00:32:20,818 --> 00:32:23,689
Did he ask you to sign
his Captain America trading cards yet?

473
00:32:23,905 --> 00:32:25,103
Trading cards?

474
00:32:25,323 --> 00:32:27,482
They're vintage. He's very proud.

475
00:32:29,244 --> 00:32:30,525
Dr Banner.

476
00:32:32,539 --> 00:32:33,820
Yeah, hi.

477
00:32:34,374 --> 00:32:35,572
They told me you would be coming.

478
00:32:35,792 --> 00:32:37,073
Word is, you can find the Cube.

479
00:32:38,128 --> 00:32:40,002
Is that the only word on me?

480
00:32:40,422 --> 00:32:41,585
Only word I care about.

481
00:32:44,176 --> 00:32:46,763
It must be strange for you, all of this.

482
00:32:47,472 --> 00:32:50,141
Well, this is actually kind of familiar.

483
00:32:50,350 --> 00:32:52,923
Gentlemen, you might want
to step inside in a minute.

484
00:32:53,144 --> 00:32:55,896
It's going to get a little hard to breathe.

485
00:32:57,148 --> 00:32:58,690
<i>Flight crew, secure the deck.</i>

486
00:33:03,196 --> 00:33:04,774
Is this a submarine?

487
00:33:05,323 --> 00:33:06,319
Really?

488
00:33:06,449 --> 00:33:10,199
They want me in a submerged,
pressurised, metal container?

489
00:33:36,606 --> 00:33:38,979
No, no, this is much worse.

490
00:34:08,807 --> 00:34:11,512
Hover power check complete.
Position cyclic.

491
00:34:11,727 --> 00:34:14,135
Increase collective to 8.0%.

492
00:34:19,234 --> 00:34:21,523
Preparing for maximum
performance takeoff.

493
00:34:21,654 --> 00:34:23,148
Increase output to capacity.

494
00:34:23,322 --> 00:34:25,445
Power plant performing at capacity.

495
00:34:25,658 --> 00:34:27,116
We are clear.

496
00:34:27,326 --> 00:34:28,821
All engines operating.

497
00:34:29,037 --> 00:34:33,663
S.H.I.E.L.D. Emergency
Protocol 193.6 in effect.

498
00:34:33,917 --> 00:34:36,455
- We are at level, sir.
- Good.

499
00:34:36,836 --> 00:34:37,832
Let's vanish.

500
00:34:38,046 --> 00:34:40,454
Engage retro-reflection panels.

501
00:34:56,232 --> 00:34:57,394
Reflection panels engaged.

502
00:34:58,025 --> 00:34:59,401
Gentlemen.

503
00:35:11,748 --> 00:35:12,863
Doctor, thank you for coming.

504
00:35:14,877 --> 00:35:16,750
Thanks for asking nicely.

505
00:35:16,962 --> 00:35:19,583
So, how long am I staying?

506
00:35:19,798 --> 00:35:21,589
Once we get our hands on
the Tesseract,

507
00:35:21,717 --> 00:35:22,915
you're in the wind.

508
00:35:23,051 --> 00:35:24,878
Where are you with that?

509
00:35:25,095 --> 00:35:26,838
We're sweeping every
wirelessly accessible

510
00:35:26,972 --> 00:35:27,968
camera on the planet.

511
00:35:28,558 --> 00:35:30,349
Cell phones, laptops...

512
00:35:30,894 --> 00:35:34,179
If it's connected to a satellite,
it's eyes and ears for us.

513
00:35:34,397 --> 00:35:35,642
That's still not gonna find them in time.

514
00:35:35,857 --> 00:35:36,853
You have to narrow your field.

515
00:35:37,066 --> 00:35:39,024
How many spectrometers
do you have access to?

516
00:35:39,235 --> 00:35:40,860
- How many are there?
- Call every lab you know.

517
00:35:41,070 --> 00:35:42,778
Tell them to put
the spectrometers on the roof

518
00:35:42,906 --> 00:35:44,364
and calibrate them for gamma rays.

519
00:35:44,574 --> 00:35:47,777
I'll rough out a tracking algorithm,
basic cluster recognition.

520
00:35:48,077 --> 00:35:50,486
At least we could rule out a few places.

521
00:35:50,748 --> 00:35:52,539
Do you have somewhere
for me to work?

522
00:35:52,792 --> 00:35:53,906
Agent Romanoff,

523
00:35:54,084 --> 00:35:56,326
could you show Dr Banner
to his laboratory, please?

524
00:35:57,463 --> 00:35:59,705
You're gonna love it, Doc.
We got all the toys.

525
00:36:00,257 --> 00:36:02,049
Put it over there.

526
00:36:04,053 --> 00:36:06,176
Where did you find all these people?

527
00:36:06,388 --> 00:36:09,344
S.H.I.E.L.D. has no shortage
of enemies, Doctor.

528
00:36:09,810 --> 00:36:10,889
Is this the stuff you need?

529
00:36:11,061 --> 00:36:12,057
Yeah, iridium.

530
00:36:12,229 --> 00:36:14,850
It's found in meteorites.
It forms anti-protons.

531
00:36:15,065 --> 00:36:16,689
It's very hard to get hold of.

532
00:36:16,900 --> 00:36:18,442
Especially if S.H.I.E.L.D.
knows you need it.

533
00:36:18,652 --> 00:36:20,027
Well, I didn't know.

534
00:36:20,237 --> 00:36:21,435
Hey!

535
00:36:21,655 --> 00:36:23,944
The Tesseract has shown me so much.

536
00:36:24,408 --> 00:36:26,317
It's more than knowledge. It's truth.

537
00:36:26,451 --> 00:36:27,447
I know.

538
00:36:28,286 --> 00:36:30,197
What did it show you, Agent Barton?

539
00:36:31,165 --> 00:36:32,576
My next target.

540
00:36:32,750 --> 00:36:33,746
Tell me what you need.

541
00:36:37,255 --> 00:36:39,082
I need a distraction.

542
00:36:40,007 --> 00:36:41,418
And an eyeball.

543
00:36:48,182 --> 00:36:50,721
I mean, if it's not too much trouble.

544
00:36:50,936 --> 00:36:51,967
No, no. It's fine.

545
00:36:55,024 --> 00:36:56,601
It's a vintage set.

546
00:36:56,817 --> 00:36:59,106
It took me a couple of years
to collect them all.

547
00:37:01,655 --> 00:37:02,734
Near mint.

548
00:37:02,948 --> 00:37:04,323
Slight foxing around the edges, but...

549
00:37:04,533 --> 00:37:07,154
We got a hit. A 67% match.

550
00:37:07,661 --> 00:37:09,286
Wait. Cross match, 79%.

551
00:37:10,290 --> 00:37:11,286
Location?

552
00:37:11,458 --> 00:37:14,494
Stuttgart, Germany. 28 Königstrasse.

553
00:37:14,711 --> 00:37:15,956
He's not exactly hiding.

554
00:37:16,171 --> 00:37:17,285
Captain,

555
00:37:17,631 --> 00:37:18,626
you're up.

556
00:39:54,170 --> 00:39:55,285
Kneel before me.

557
00:39:59,759 --> 00:40:01,040
I said

558
00:40:03,138 --> 00:40:05,296
kneel!

559
00:40:14,609 --> 00:40:17,978
Is not this simpler?

560
00:40:19,530 --> 00:40:22,733
Is this not your natural state?

561
00:40:25,036 --> 00:40:28,239
It's the unspoken truth of humanity,

562
00:40:28,456 --> 00:40:30,828
that you crave subjugation.

563
00:40:31,375 --> 00:40:35,160
The bright lure of freedom
diminishes your life's joy

564
00:40:35,380 --> 00:40:37,954
in a mad scramble for power,

565
00:40:39,801 --> 00:40:41,177
for identity.

566
00:40:42,846 --> 00:40:46,180
You were made to be ruled.

567
00:40:46,808 --> 00:40:48,433
In the end,

568
00:40:48,685 --> 00:40:50,974
you will always kneel.

569
00:40:58,363 --> 00:41:00,320
Not to men like you.

570
00:41:01,366 --> 00:41:03,275
There are no men like me.

571
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:07,031
There are always men like you.

572
00:41:08,331 --> 00:41:10,158
Look to your elder, people.

573
00:41:12,377 --> 00:41:13,789
Let him be an example.

574
00:41:20,594 --> 00:41:23,168
You know, the last time
I was in Germany,

575
00:41:23,389 --> 00:41:26,556
and saw a man standing
above everybody else,

576
00:41:26,767 --> 00:41:28,226
we ended up disagreeing.

577
00:41:28,436 --> 00:41:30,393
The soldier.

578
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:33,685
The man out of time.

579
00:41:34,276 --> 00:41:35,521
I'm not the one who's out of time.

580
00:41:39,030 --> 00:41:41,568
<i>Loki, drop the weapon
and stand down.</i>

581
00:42:01,929 --> 00:42:03,507
Kneel.

582
00:42:03,639 --> 00:42:05,050
Not today!

583
00:42:07,143 --> 00:42:08,423
The guy's all over the place.

584
00:42:11,939 --> 00:42:14,265
<i>Agent Romanoff. You miss me?</i>

585
00:42:31,001 --> 00:42:33,077
<i>Make your move, Reindeer Games.</i>

586
00:42:41,137 --> 00:42:42,596
<i>Good move.</i>

587
00:42:44,099 --> 00:42:45,379
Mr Stark.

588
00:42:46,059 --> 00:42:47,222
<i>Captain.</i>

589
00:42:54,442 --> 00:42:56,068
<i>Is he saying anything?</i>

590
00:42:56,279 --> 00:42:57,524
Not a word.

591
00:42:57,822 --> 00:42:59,731
<i>Just get him here. We're low on time.</i>

592
00:43:02,785 --> 00:43:03,781
I don't like it.

593
00:43:04,161 --> 00:43:06,119
What, Rock of Ages
giving up so easily?

594
00:43:06,330 --> 00:43:07,990
I don't remember it being that easy.

595
00:43:08,165 --> 00:43:09,624
This guy packs a wallop.

596
00:43:09,834 --> 00:43:13,417
Still, you are pretty spry
for an older fellow.

597
00:43:14,463 --> 00:43:16,042
What's your thing, Pilates?

598
00:43:16,216 --> 00:43:17,212
What?

599
00:43:17,384 --> 00:43:18,380
It's like calisthenics.

600
00:43:18,510 --> 00:43:20,550
You might have missed
a couple of things

601
00:43:20,762 --> 00:43:22,387
doing time as a Capsicle.

602
00:43:24,308 --> 00:43:25,885
Fury didn't tell me
he was calling you in.

603
00:43:26,101 --> 00:43:28,972
Yeah, there's a lot of things
Fury doesn't tell you.

604
00:43:29,354 --> 00:43:30,932
Where's this coming from?

605
00:43:35,027 --> 00:43:37,601
What's the matter? Are you
scared of a little lightning?

606
00:43:38,031 --> 00:43:40,319
I'm not overly fond of what follows.

607
00:43:58,135 --> 00:43:59,298
What are you doing?

608
00:44:12,233 --> 00:44:13,691
<i>And now there's that guy.</i>

609
00:44:13,901 --> 00:44:15,644
Another Asgardian?

610
00:44:15,861 --> 00:44:17,689
<i>- That guy's a friendly?
- Doesn't matter.</i>

611
00:44:17,906 --> 00:44:20,479
<i>If he frees Loki or kills him,
the Tesseract's lost.</i>

612
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:22,527
Stark, we need a plan of attack!

613
00:44:22,744 --> 00:44:25,033
<i>I have a plan. Attack.</i>

614
00:44:31,044 --> 00:44:32,836
I'd sit this one out, Cap.

615
00:44:33,046 --> 00:44:34,042
I don't see how I can.

616
00:44:34,256 --> 00:44:36,878
These guys come from legend.
They're basically gods.

617
00:44:37,343 --> 00:44:38,624
There's only one God, ma'am.

618
00:44:38,761 --> 00:44:41,133
And I'm pretty sure
he doesn't dress like that.

619
00:44:56,612 --> 00:44:57,989
Where is the Tesseract?

620
00:44:58,198 --> 00:44:59,479
I missed you, too.

621
00:44:59,700 --> 00:45:01,368
Do I look to be in a gaming mood?

622
00:45:02,077 --> 00:45:03,453
You should thank me.

623
00:45:03,912 --> 00:45:05,952
With the Bifrost gone,
how much dark energy

624
00:45:06,165 --> 00:45:08,916
did the Allfather have to
muster to conjure you here

625
00:45:09,126 --> 00:45:10,501
to your precious Earth?

626
00:45:14,631 --> 00:45:15,912
I thought you dead.

627
00:45:17,552 --> 00:45:18,963
Did you mourn?

628
00:45:19,429 --> 00:45:21,220
We all did. Our father...

629
00:45:21,556 --> 00:45:24,474
Your father.

630
00:45:26,353 --> 00:45:29,223
He did tell you
my true parentage, did he not?

631
00:45:31,775 --> 00:45:34,017
We were raised together.

632
00:45:34,235 --> 00:45:36,857
We played together,
we fought together.

633
00:45:37,365 --> 00:45:38,563
Do you remember none of that?

634
00:45:38,783 --> 00:45:40,740
I remember a shadow.

635
00:45:42,245 --> 00:45:45,281
Living in the shade of your greatness.

636
00:45:45,998 --> 00:45:48,620
I remember you tossing me
into an abyss.

637
00:45:48,751 --> 00:45:50,744
I, who was, and should be, king!

638
00:45:50,962 --> 00:45:53,038
So you take the world I love
as a recompense

639
00:45:53,172 --> 00:45:54,999
for your imagined slights?

640
00:45:55,216 --> 00:45:58,301
No. The Earth is under
my protection, Loki.

641
00:45:59,721 --> 00:46:03,256
And you're doing
a marvellous job with that.

642
00:46:03,725 --> 00:46:05,683
The humans slaughter
each other in droves

643
00:46:05,811 --> 00:46:07,602
while you idly fret.

644
00:46:07,813 --> 00:46:09,971
I mean to rule them,
as why should I not?

645
00:46:10,190 --> 00:46:11,732
You think yourself above them?

646
00:46:12,818 --> 00:46:13,814
Well, yes.

647
00:46:14,027 --> 00:46:16,483
Then you miss the truth
of ruling, brother.

648
00:46:17,322 --> 00:46:18,699
A throne would suit you ill.

649
00:46:23,913 --> 00:46:26,665
I've seen worlds
you've never known about!

650
00:46:26,875 --> 00:46:31,038
I have grown, Odinson, in my exile.

651
00:46:31,421 --> 00:46:33,378
I have seen the true power
of the Tesseract,

652
00:46:33,506 --> 00:46:34,585
and when I wield it...

653
00:46:34,799 --> 00:46:36,543
Who showed you this power?

654
00:46:37,719 --> 00:46:39,048
Who controls the would-be king?

655
00:46:39,263 --> 00:46:41,054
- I am a king!
- Not here!

656
00:46:41,265 --> 00:46:42,545
You give up the Tesseract!

657
00:46:42,683 --> 00:46:45,221
You give up this poisonous dream!

658
00:46:47,938 --> 00:46:49,314
You come home.

659
00:46:54,278 --> 00:46:55,393
I don't have it.

660
00:46:57,490 --> 00:46:59,282
You need the Cube to bring me home.

661
00:46:59,409 --> 00:47:01,734
But I've sent it off, I know not where.

662
00:47:02,871 --> 00:47:04,698
You listen well, brother.

663
00:47:06,666 --> 00:47:07,865
I'm listening.

664
00:47:17,010 --> 00:47:18,670
Do not touch me again.

665
00:47:18,888 --> 00:47:20,466
Then don't take my stuff.

666
00:47:20,682 --> 00:47:22,923
You have no idea
what you're dealing with.

667
00:47:24,811 --> 00:47:25,806
Shakespeare in the Park?

668
00:47:27,188 --> 00:47:30,308
Doth Mother know
you wear-eth her drapes?

669
00:47:30,566 --> 00:47:33,318
This is beyond you, metal man.

670
00:47:33,528 --> 00:47:35,651
Loki will face Asgardian justice.

671
00:47:35,863 --> 00:47:39,233
He gives up the Cube,
he's all yours. Until then,

672
00:47:39,618 --> 00:47:40,863
<i>stay out of the way.</i>

673
00:47:42,413 --> 00:47:44,037
<i>Tourist.</i>

674
00:47:49,420 --> 00:47:50,451
Okay.

675
00:48:20,244 --> 00:48:23,162
Power at 400% capacity.

676
00:48:23,372 --> 00:48:24,914
How about that?

677
00:49:25,229 --> 00:49:26,427
Hey!

678
00:49:28,983 --> 00:49:30,181
That's enough.

679
00:49:34,071 --> 00:49:35,779
Now, I don't know
what you plan on doing here.

680
00:49:35,990 --> 00:49:38,278
I've come here to put an end
to Loki's schemes.

681
00:49:38,492 --> 00:49:41,031
Then prove it. Put that hammer down.

682
00:49:41,163 --> 00:49:42,158
Yeah... No.

683
00:49:42,414 --> 00:49:43,873
<i>Bad call. He loves his hammer.</i>

684
00:49:45,459 --> 00:49:47,700
You want me to put the hammer down?

685
00:50:15,073 --> 00:50:16,733
Are we done, here?

686
00:51:04,625 --> 00:51:07,579
In case it's unclear,

687
00:51:08,296 --> 00:51:10,087
if you try to escape,

688
00:51:11,173 --> 00:51:13,462
if you so much as scratch that glass,

689
00:51:23,061 --> 00:51:27,011
it's 30,000 feet straight down
in a steel trap.

690
00:51:27,566 --> 00:51:29,689
You get how that works?

691
00:51:31,737 --> 00:51:34,358
Ant, boot.

692
00:51:37,701 --> 00:51:39,444
It's an impressive cage.

693
00:51:40,370 --> 00:51:42,993
Not built, I think, for me.

694
00:51:43,374 --> 00:51:45,782
Built for something
a lot stronger than you.

695
00:51:46,002 --> 00:51:47,876
Oh, I've heard.

696
00:51:48,880 --> 00:51:50,043
<i>A mindless beast.</i>

697
00:51:51,049 --> 00:51:52,673
<i>Makes play he's still a man.</i>

698
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:56,002
<i>How desperate are you,</i>

699
00:51:56,221 --> 00:51:59,305
<i>that you call on such
lost creatures to defend you?</i>

700
00:51:59,516 --> 00:52:01,841
<i>How desperate am I?</i>

701
00:52:02,060 --> 00:52:03,852
You threaten my world with war.

702
00:52:04,063 --> 00:52:06,186
You steal a force
you can't hope to control.

703
00:52:06,398 --> 00:52:10,182
You talk about peace,
and you kill because it's fun.

704
00:52:10,402 --> 00:52:13,403
You have made me very desperate.

705
00:52:13,614 --> 00:52:15,523
You might not be glad that you did.

706
00:52:18,786 --> 00:52:22,071
It burns you to have come so close.

707
00:52:23,542 --> 00:52:26,246
To have the Tesseract, to have power,

708
00:52:27,045 --> 00:52:29,252
unlimited power.

709
00:52:29,464 --> 00:52:31,421
And for what?

710
00:52:33,093 --> 00:52:36,886
A warm light for all mankind to share.

711
00:52:37,139 --> 00:52:40,389
And then to be reminded
what real power is.

712
00:52:44,480 --> 00:52:48,774
Well, let me know if "real power"
wants a magazine or something.

713
00:52:57,118 --> 00:52:58,577
He really grows on you, doesn't he?

714
00:52:58,786 --> 00:53:00,695
Loki's gonna drag this out.

715
00:53:00,913 --> 00:53:04,366
So, Thor, what's his play?

716
00:53:04,585 --> 00:53:07,123
He has an army called the Chitauri.

717
00:53:07,338 --> 00:53:10,255
They're not of Asgard,
nor any world known.

718
00:53:10,674 --> 00:53:12,750
He means to lead them
against your people.

719
00:53:12,968 --> 00:53:14,546
They will win him the Earth,

720
00:53:14,678 --> 00:53:16,470
in return, I suspect, for the Tesseract.

721
00:53:16,680 --> 00:53:18,424
An army

722
00:53:18,641 --> 00:53:20,301
from outer space.

723
00:53:20,517 --> 00:53:22,925
So, he's building another portal.

724
00:53:23,145 --> 00:53:24,474
That's what he needs Erik Selvig for.

725
00:53:24,606 --> 00:53:25,602
Selvig?

726
00:53:25,774 --> 00:53:28,099
- He's an astrophysicist.
- He's a friend.

727
00:53:28,318 --> 00:53:30,441
Loki has him under some kind of spell,

728
00:53:30,612 --> 00:53:32,106
along with one of ours.

729
00:53:32,322 --> 00:53:33,900
I want to know why Loki let us take him.

730
00:53:34,032 --> 00:53:35,312
He's not leading an army from here.

731
00:53:35,533 --> 00:53:37,241
I don't think
we should be focusing on Loki.

732
00:53:37,452 --> 00:53:39,243
That guy's brain is a bag full of cats.

733
00:53:39,371 --> 00:53:40,651
You could smell crazy on him.

734
00:53:40,872 --> 00:53:42,616
Have care how you speak.

735
00:53:43,166 --> 00:53:45,373
Loki is beyond reason,
but he is of Asgard.

736
00:53:45,795 --> 00:53:46,874
And he is my brother.

737
00:53:47,088 --> 00:53:48,961
He killed 80 people in two days.

738
00:53:49,840 --> 00:53:50,836
He's adopted.

739
00:53:51,008 --> 00:53:53,297
I think it's about the mechanics.

740
00:53:53,511 --> 00:53:55,468
Iridium... What do they
need the iridium for?

741
00:53:55,680 --> 00:53:56,675
It's a stabilising agent.

742
00:53:56,847 --> 00:53:58,128
I'm just saying, pick a weekend.

743
00:53:58,266 --> 00:53:59,808
I'll fly you to Portland.

744
00:54:00,017 --> 00:54:01,559
Keep love alive.

745
00:54:01,769 --> 00:54:03,643
It means the portal
won't collapse on itself

746
00:54:03,813 --> 00:54:05,641
like it did at S.H.I.E.L.D.

747
00:54:05,858 --> 00:54:09,143
No hard feelings, Point Break.
You've got a mean swing.

748
00:54:09,361 --> 00:54:11,603
Also, it means the portal
can open as wide

749
00:54:11,822 --> 00:54:14,229
and stay open as long, as Loki wants.

750
00:54:14,950 --> 00:54:17,156
Raise the mizzenmast. Jib the topsails.

751
00:54:18,871 --> 00:54:20,069
<i>That man is playing Galaga.</i>

752
00:54:21,123 --> 00:54:24,492
He thought we wouldn't notice,
but we did.

753
00:54:26,462 --> 00:54:27,838
How does Fury even see these?

754
00:54:28,006 --> 00:54:29,001
He turns.

755
00:54:29,299 --> 00:54:30,923
Sounds exhausting.

756
00:54:32,010 --> 00:54:33,172
The rest of the raw materials,

757
00:54:33,386 --> 00:54:36,173
Agent Barton can get
his hands on pretty easily.

758
00:54:36,389 --> 00:54:37,764
The only major component
he still needs

759
00:54:37,974 --> 00:54:41,473
is a power source
of high-energy density.

760
00:54:41,686 --> 00:54:44,936
Something to kick-start the Cube.

761
00:54:45,148 --> 00:54:48,103
When did you become an expert
in thermonuclear astrophysics?

762
00:54:48,319 --> 00:54:49,315
Last night.

763
00:54:49,820 --> 00:54:53,023
The packet, Selvig's notes,
the extraction theory papers.

764
00:54:53,240 --> 00:54:54,236
Am I the only one who did the reading?

765
00:54:54,408 --> 00:54:57,195
Does Loki need any particular
kind of power source?

766
00:54:57,411 --> 00:55:00,116
He would have to heat the Cube
to 120-million Kelvin

767
00:55:00,331 --> 00:55:01,789
just to break through
the Coulomb barrier.

768
00:55:01,999 --> 00:55:04,205
Unless Selvig has figured out
how to stabilise

769
00:55:04,418 --> 00:55:05,534
the quantum tunnelling effect.

770
00:55:05,754 --> 00:55:06,750
Well, if he could do that,

771
00:55:06,922 --> 00:55:09,377
he could achieve heavy ion fusion
at any reactor on the planet.

772
00:55:09,591 --> 00:55:11,999
Finally, someone who speaks English.

773
00:55:12,219 --> 00:55:14,176
Is that what just happened?

774
00:55:14,388 --> 00:55:16,380
It's good to meet you, Dr Banner.

775
00:55:16,598 --> 00:55:19,634
Your work on antielectron
collisions is unparalleled.

776
00:55:19,851 --> 00:55:21,643
And I'm a huge fan of the way
you lose control

777
00:55:21,853 --> 00:55:23,893
and turn into an enormous
green rage-monster.

778
00:55:25,440 --> 00:55:26,473
Thanks.

779
00:55:26,693 --> 00:55:29,184
Dr Banner is only here
to track the Cube.

780
00:55:29,404 --> 00:55:30,684
I was hoping you might join him.

781
00:55:30,905 --> 00:55:32,068
I would start with that stick of his.

782
00:55:32,198 --> 00:55:33,229
It may be magical,

783
00:55:33,366 --> 00:55:34,646
but it works an awful lot
like a HYDRA weapon.

784
00:55:34,784 --> 00:55:37,820
I don't know about that,
but it is powered by the Cube.

785
00:55:38,121 --> 00:55:39,864
And I would like to know
how Loki used it

786
00:55:40,081 --> 00:55:41,659
to turn two of the sharpest men I know

787
00:55:41,791 --> 00:55:43,582
into his personal flying monkeys.

788
00:55:43,960 --> 00:55:45,502
Monkeys? I do not understand.

789
00:55:45,628 --> 00:55:46,625
I do.

790
00:55:49,633 --> 00:55:51,507
I understood that reference.

791
00:55:52,428 --> 00:55:53,756
Shall we play, Doctor?

792
00:55:53,971 --> 00:55:55,679
This way, sir.

793
00:56:09,654 --> 00:56:11,232
The gamma readings
are definitely consistent

794
00:56:11,448 --> 00:56:13,440
with Selvig's reports of the Tesseract.

795
00:56:13,825 --> 00:56:15,450
But it's going to take weeks to process.

796
00:56:15,660 --> 00:56:16,858
If we bypass their mainframe

797
00:56:16,995 --> 00:56:18,275
and direct route to the Homer cluster,

798
00:56:18,496 --> 00:56:21,581
we can clock this
at around 600 teraflops.

799
00:56:22,751 --> 00:56:24,708
All I packed was a toothbrush.

800
00:56:25,795 --> 00:56:27,374
You know, you should come by
Stark Tower sometime.

801
00:56:27,590 --> 00:56:29,629
Top ten floors, all R&D.

802
00:56:29,967 --> 00:56:31,426
You'd love it. It's Candy Land.

803
00:56:31,636 --> 00:56:34,127
Thanks, but the last time
I was in New York,

804
00:56:34,347 --> 00:56:36,885
I kind of broke Harlem.

805
00:56:37,099 --> 00:56:38,926
Well, I promise
a stress-free environment.

806
00:56:39,143 --> 00:56:40,934
No tension, no surprises.

807
00:56:42,438 --> 00:56:43,932
- Hey!
- Nothing?

808
00:56:44,148 --> 00:56:45,144
Are you nuts?

809
00:56:45,274 --> 00:56:46,270
Jury's out.

810
00:56:46,400 --> 00:56:47,516
You really have got
a lid on it, haven't you?

811
00:56:47,653 --> 00:56:48,648
What's your secret?

812
00:56:48,779 --> 00:56:50,238
Mellow jazz, bongo drums,
huge bag of weed?

813
00:56:50,405 --> 00:56:51,520
Is everything a joke to you?

814
00:56:51,823 --> 00:56:52,819
Funny things are.

815
00:56:52,950 --> 00:56:54,693
Threatening the safety
of everyone on this ship

816
00:56:54,826 --> 00:56:56,071
isn't funny.

817
00:56:56,203 --> 00:56:57,199
No offence, Doc.

818
00:56:57,329 --> 00:56:58,823
It's all right,
I wouldn't have come aboard

819
00:56:58,956 --> 00:57:01,791
if I couldn't handle pointy things.

820
00:57:01,917 --> 00:57:04,490
You're tip-toeing, big man.
You need to strut.

821
00:57:04,628 --> 00:57:06,288
And you need to focus
on the problem, Mr Stark.

822
00:57:06,421 --> 00:57:07,917
Do you think I'm not?

823
00:57:08,049 --> 00:57:10,836
Why did Fury call us in?
Why now? Why not before?

824
00:57:10,969 --> 00:57:12,712
What isn't he telling us?

825
00:57:12,846 --> 00:57:14,589
I can't do the equation unless
I have all the variables.

826
00:57:15,223 --> 00:57:16,468
You think Fury's hiding something?

827
00:57:16,599 --> 00:57:19,766
He's a spy. Captain, he's "the" spy.

828
00:57:19,894 --> 00:57:21,638
His secrets have secrets.

829
00:57:21,771 --> 00:57:23,265
It's bugging him, too. Isn't it?

830
00:57:25,859 --> 00:57:27,651
I just want to finish my work here, and...

831
00:57:27,778 --> 00:57:28,774
Doctor?

832
00:57:34,201 --> 00:57:36,573
"A warm light for all mankind."

833
00:57:36,704 --> 00:57:38,780
Loki's jab at Fury about the Cube.

834
00:57:38,914 --> 00:57:40,373
I heard it.

835
00:57:40,499 --> 00:57:42,788
I think that was meant for you.

836
00:57:43,502 --> 00:57:46,456
Even if Barton didn't
tell Loki about the tower,

837
00:57:46,589 --> 00:57:47,668
it was still all over the news.

838
00:57:47,799 --> 00:57:49,875
The Stark Tower? That big, ugly

839
00:57:51,219 --> 00:57:52,464
building in New York?

840
00:57:52,596 --> 00:57:56,296
It's powered by an arc reactor,
a self-sustaining energy source.

841
00:57:56,433 --> 00:57:58,840
That building will run itself
for, what, a year?

842
00:57:58,977 --> 00:58:00,804
It's just the prototype.

843
00:58:00,937 --> 00:58:02,895
I'm kind of the only name
in clean energy right now.

844
00:58:03,315 --> 00:58:04,726
That's what he's getting at.

845
00:58:04,858 --> 00:58:07,431
So, why didn't S.H.I.E.L.D. bring him in
on the Tesseract project?

846
00:58:07,569 --> 00:58:09,313
What are they doing
in the energy business

847
00:58:09,447 --> 00:58:10,775
in the first place?

848
00:58:10,907 --> 00:58:13,861
I should probably look into that
once my decryption programme

849
00:58:13,993 --> 00:58:16,152
finishes breaking into all of
S.H.I.E.L.D.'s secure files.

850
00:58:16,287 --> 00:58:17,283
I'm sorry. Did you say...

851
00:58:17,413 --> 00:58:19,406
Jarvis has been running it
since I hit the bridge.

852
00:58:19,540 --> 00:58:21,118
In a few hours,
I'll know every dirty secret

853
00:58:21,250 --> 00:58:22,413
S.H.I.E.L.D. has ever tried to hide.

854
00:58:22,543 --> 00:58:23,539
Blueberry?

855
00:58:23,669 --> 00:58:25,543
Yet you're confused about why
they didn't want you around.

856
00:58:25,671 --> 00:58:28,508
An intelligence organisation
that fears intelligence?

857
00:58:28,634 --> 00:58:30,211
Historically, not awesome.

858
00:58:30,344 --> 00:58:32,633
I think Loki's trying to wind us up.

859
00:58:32,763 --> 00:58:34,341
This is a man who means to start a war

860
00:58:34,473 --> 00:58:36,015
and if we don't stay focused,
he'll succeed.

861
00:58:37,309 --> 00:58:39,765
We have orders.
We should follow them.

862
00:58:40,270 --> 00:58:42,263
Following's not really my style.

863
00:58:43,482 --> 00:58:45,854
And you're all about style, aren't you?

864
00:58:45,985 --> 00:58:47,016
Of the people in this room,

865
00:58:47,152 --> 00:58:48,731
which one is,
A, wearing a spangly outfit,

866
00:58:48,863 --> 00:58:50,192
and, B, not of use?

867
00:58:50,323 --> 00:58:54,653
Steve, tell me none of this
smells a little funky to you.

868
00:58:57,372 --> 00:58:58,403
Just find the Cube.

869
00:59:11,345 --> 00:59:13,254
That's the guy
my dad never shut up about?

870
00:59:13,723 --> 00:59:16,510
I'm wondering if they shouldn't have
kept him on ice.

871
00:59:17,351 --> 00:59:19,059
The guy's not wrong about Loki.

872
00:59:19,186 --> 00:59:20,930
He does have the jump on us.

873
00:59:21,063 --> 00:59:23,768
What he's got is an Acme dynamite kit.

874
00:59:23,900 --> 00:59:25,726
It's going to blow up in his face.

875
00:59:25,860 --> 00:59:28,149
And I'm going to be there when it does.

876
00:59:28,446 --> 00:59:30,605
Yeah. I'll read all about it.

877
00:59:32,743 --> 00:59:34,023
Or you'll be suiting up
with the rest of us.

878
00:59:35,621 --> 00:59:39,203
You see, I don't get a suit of armour.

879
00:59:39,333 --> 00:59:42,666
I'm exposed. Like a nerve.

880
00:59:42,794 --> 00:59:44,538
It's a nightmare.

881
00:59:44,671 --> 00:59:47,458
I've got a cluster of shrapnel
trying every second

882
00:59:47,591 --> 00:59:49,585
to crawl its way into my heart.

883
00:59:49,719 --> 00:59:51,759
This stops it.

884
00:59:51,888 --> 00:59:54,213
This little circle of light,
it's part of me now,

885
00:59:55,433 --> 00:59:57,093
not just armour.

886
00:59:57,769 --> 01:00:00,224
It's a terrible privilege.

887
01:00:00,563 --> 01:00:02,935
- But you can control it.
- Because I learned how.

888
01:00:03,066 --> 01:00:04,062
It's different.

889
01:00:04,400 --> 01:00:07,734
Hey, I read all about your accident.

890
01:00:07,862 --> 01:00:11,197
That much gamma exposure
should have killed you.

891
01:00:11,325 --> 01:00:13,781
So you're saying that the Hulk...

892
01:00:15,246 --> 01:00:17,618
The other guy saved my life?

893
01:00:18,124 --> 01:00:19,238
That's nice.

894
01:00:20,126 --> 01:00:23,910
It's a nice sentiment. Saved it for what?

895
01:00:25,214 --> 01:00:27,123
I guess we'll find out.

896
01:00:28,843 --> 01:00:30,504
You may not enjoy that.

897
01:00:30,637 --> 01:00:32,594
And you just might.

898
01:01:31,826 --> 01:01:33,202
<i>As soon as Loki took the doctor,</i>

899
01:01:33,328 --> 01:01:35,071
we moved Jane Foster.

900
01:01:35,205 --> 01:01:37,577
They've got an excellent
observatory in Tromsø.

901
01:01:37,707 --> 01:01:41,242
She was asked to consult there
very suddenly yesterday.

902
01:01:41,378 --> 01:01:45,162
Handsome fee, private plane,
very remote.

903
01:01:46,049 --> 01:01:47,080
She'll be safe.

904
01:01:47,217 --> 01:01:48,592
Thank you.

905
01:01:50,387 --> 01:01:52,427
It's no accident, Loki taking Erik Selvig.

906
01:01:53,432 --> 01:01:56,006
I dread what he plans for him
once he's done.

907
01:01:56,143 --> 01:01:57,258
Erik is a good man.

908
01:01:57,395 --> 01:01:58,390
He talks about you a lot.

909
01:02:00,273 --> 01:02:02,265
You changed his life.

910
01:02:03,985 --> 01:02:05,858
You changed everything around here.

911
01:02:05,987 --> 01:02:08,110
They were better as they were.

912
01:02:08,698 --> 01:02:10,774
We pretend on Asgard
that we're more advanced

913
01:02:10,908 --> 01:02:14,610
but we come here,
battling like bilge snipe.

914
01:02:14,746 --> 01:02:16,573
- Like what?
- Bilge snipe.

915
01:02:16,707 --> 01:02:19,743
You know, huge, scaly, big antlers.

916
01:02:20,544 --> 01:02:22,335
- You don't have those?
- I don't think so.

917
01:02:22,462 --> 01:02:24,336
Well, they are repulsive.

918
01:02:25,674 --> 01:02:27,916
And they trample everything
in their path.

919
01:02:35,602 --> 01:02:38,935
When I first came to Earth,
Loki's rage followed me here,

920
01:02:39,063 --> 01:02:41,389
and your people paid the price.

921
01:02:41,524 --> 01:02:43,316
And now, again.

922
01:02:45,862 --> 01:02:48,317
In my youth, I courted war.

923
01:02:50,074 --> 01:02:52,067
War hasn't started yet.

924
01:02:53,204 --> 01:02:54,995
You think you could make Loki tell us

925
01:02:55,122 --> 01:02:56,403
where the Tesseract is?

926
01:02:56,540 --> 01:02:59,790
I do not know. Loki's mind is far afield.

927
01:02:59,919 --> 01:03:04,628
It's not just power he craves,
it's vengeance, upon me.

928
01:03:04,757 --> 01:03:06,880
There's no pain
would prise his need from him.

929
01:03:07,968 --> 01:03:10,175
A lot of guys think that

930
01:03:10,304 --> 01:03:11,798
until the pain starts.

931
01:03:14,101 --> 01:03:15,595
What are you asking me to do?

932
01:03:15,727 --> 01:03:19,310
I'm asking,
what are you prepared to do?

933
01:03:19,439 --> 01:03:20,470
Loki is a prisoner.

934
01:03:20,607 --> 01:03:22,932
Then why do I feel like
he's the only person on this boat

935
01:03:23,068 --> 01:03:24,645
that wants to be here?

936
01:03:37,250 --> 01:03:40,334
There's not many people
who can sneak up on me.

937
01:03:40,461 --> 01:03:42,121
But you figured I'd come.

938
01:03:42,797 --> 01:03:44,375
After.

939
01:03:45,258 --> 01:03:48,674
After whatever tortures
Fury can concoct,

940
01:03:48,803 --> 01:03:52,468
you would appear
as a friend, as a balm.

941
01:03:53,434 --> 01:03:55,094
And I would cooperate.

942
01:03:55,227 --> 01:03:57,220
I want to know what
you've done to Agent Barton.

943
01:03:57,354 --> 01:03:59,347
I would say I've expanded his mind.

944
01:04:01,942 --> 01:04:03,851
And once you've won,

945
01:04:04,737 --> 01:04:06,017
once you're king of the mountain,

946
01:04:08,157 --> 01:04:10,648
what happens to his mind?

947
01:04:11,910 --> 01:04:13,703
Is this love, Agent Romanoff?

948
01:04:13,830 --> 01:04:16,665
Love is for children. I owe him a debt.

949
01:04:20,545 --> 01:04:22,419
Tell me.

950
01:04:26,760 --> 01:04:30,010
Before I worked for S.H.I.E.L. D... I...

951
01:04:32,432 --> 01:04:36,347
Well, I made a name for myself.

952
01:04:36,479 --> 01:04:39,480
I have a very specific skill set.

953
01:04:39,607 --> 01:04:43,272
I didn't care who I used it for, or on.

954
01:04:44,278 --> 01:04:47,778
I got on S.H.I.E.L.D.'s radar
in a bad way.

955
01:04:48,950 --> 01:04:51,867
Agent Barton was sent to kill me.

956
01:04:52,912 --> 01:04:54,455
He made a different call.

957
01:04:56,416 --> 01:04:59,453
And what will you do
if I vow to spare him?

958
01:04:59,836 --> 01:05:01,165
Not let you out.

959
01:05:01,296 --> 01:05:03,170
No, but I like this.

960
01:05:04,091 --> 01:05:07,507
Your world in the balance,
and you bargain for one man.

961
01:05:07,636 --> 01:05:09,712
Regimes fall every day.

962
01:05:09,847 --> 01:05:12,384
I tend not to weep over that.
I'm Russian.

963
01:05:12,516 --> 01:05:13,512
Or I was.

964
01:05:14,811 --> 01:05:16,471
And what are you now?

965
01:05:16,938 --> 01:05:19,892
It's really not that complicated.

966
01:05:20,024 --> 01:05:24,105
I got red in my ledger,
I'd like to wipe it out.

967
01:05:25,113 --> 01:05:26,655
Can you?

968
01:05:27,991 --> 01:05:31,775
Can you wipe out that much red?

969
01:05:32,954 --> 01:05:34,746
Dreykov's daughter,

970
01:05:36,167 --> 01:05:37,993
São Paulo,

971
01:05:39,044 --> 01:05:41,535
the hospital fire?

972
01:05:42,381 --> 01:05:44,753
Barton told me everything.

973
01:05:44,884 --> 01:05:47,968
Your ledger is dripping. It's gushing red

974
01:05:48,095 --> 01:05:50,586
and you think saving a man
no more virtuous than yourself

975
01:05:50,723 --> 01:05:52,098
will change anything?

976
01:05:52,224 --> 01:05:54,895
This is the basest sentimentality.

977
01:05:55,020 --> 01:05:57,262
This is a child at prayer.

978
01:05:57,397 --> 01:05:58,678
Pathetic!

979
01:05:59,483 --> 01:06:02,056
<i>You lie and kill</i>

980
01:06:02,194 --> 01:06:05,230
<i>in the service of liars and killers.</i>

981
01:06:08,325 --> 01:06:11,491
<i>You pretend to be separate,
to have your own code,</i>

982
01:06:11,620 --> 01:06:14,325
<i>something that makes up
for the horrors.</i>

983
01:06:15,500 --> 01:06:17,907
<i>But they are part of you.</i>

984
01:06:18,044 --> 01:06:21,828
<i>And they will never go away.</i>

985
01:06:22,423 --> 01:06:25,923
I won't touch Barton,
not until I make him kill you.

986
01:06:26,052 --> 01:06:28,294
Slowly, intimately,

987
01:06:28,429 --> 01:06:30,801
in every way he knows you fear.

988
01:06:30,932 --> 01:06:34,016
And then he'll wake just long
enough to see his good work

989
01:06:34,143 --> 01:06:37,596
and when he screams, I'll split his skull.

990
01:06:37,731 --> 01:06:40,851
This is my bargain, you mewling quim.

991
01:06:42,444 --> 01:06:44,022
You're a monster.

992
01:06:46,240 --> 01:06:47,734
Oh, no.

993
01:06:48,617 --> 01:06:50,195
You brought the monster.

994
01:06:53,205 --> 01:06:54,783
So, Banner.

995
01:06:55,834 --> 01:06:56,996
That's your play.

996
01:06:57,127 --> 01:06:58,158
What?

997
01:06:59,129 --> 01:07:00,789
Loki means to unleash the Hulk.

998
01:07:00,922 --> 01:07:02,381
Keep Banner in the lab. I'm on my way.

999
01:07:02,507 --> 01:07:03,586
Send Thor as well.

1000
01:07:05,260 --> 01:07:06,588
Thank you

1001
01:07:06,720 --> 01:07:08,878
for your cooperation.

1002
01:07:16,397 --> 01:07:17,856
What are you doing, Mr Stark?

1003
01:07:17,982 --> 01:07:20,473
Kind of been wondering
the same thing about you.

1004
01:07:20,610 --> 01:07:22,483
You're supposed to be locating
the Tesseract.

1005
01:07:22,612 --> 01:07:24,189
We are. The model's locked

1006
01:07:24,322 --> 01:07:25,602
and we're sweeping
for the signature now.

1007
01:07:25,740 --> 01:07:26,735
When we get a hit,

1008
01:07:26,866 --> 01:07:28,823
we'll have the location
within half a mile.

1009
01:07:28,951 --> 01:07:33,197
Yeah, then you get your
Cube back. No muss, no fuss.

1010
01:07:33,331 --> 01:07:34,445
What is "Phase 2"?

1011
01:07:36,668 --> 01:07:39,503
Phase 2 is S.H.I.E.L.D. uses
the Cube to make weapons.

1012
01:07:39,630 --> 01:07:41,373
Sorry, computer was moving
a little slow for me.

1013
01:07:41,506 --> 01:07:44,211
Rogers, we gathered everything
related to the Tesseract.

1014
01:07:44,343 --> 01:07:45,801
This does not mean that we're making...

1015
01:07:45,928 --> 01:07:46,923
I'm sorry, Nick.

1016
01:07:47,054 --> 01:07:49,342
What were you lying?

1017
01:07:49,473 --> 01:07:50,718
I was wrong, Director.

1018
01:07:50,849 --> 01:07:51,880
The world hasn't changed a bit.

1019
01:07:52,017 --> 01:07:53,048
Did you know about this?

1020
01:07:53,185 --> 01:07:54,513
You want to think about
removing yourself

1021
01:07:54,645 --> 01:07:55,973
from this environment, Doctor?

1022
01:07:56,104 --> 01:07:58,264
I was in Calcutta.
I was pretty well removed.

1023
01:07:58,399 --> 01:07:59,562
Loki is manipulating you.

1024
01:07:59,692 --> 01:08:01,270
And you've been doing what, exactly?

1025
01:08:01,402 --> 01:08:03,062
You didn't come here because
I bat my eyelashes at you.

1026
01:08:03,196 --> 01:08:04,311
Yes, and I'm not leaving

1027
01:08:04,447 --> 01:08:05,728
because suddenly
you get a little twitchy.

1028
01:08:05,865 --> 01:08:07,490
I'd like to know why S.H.I.E.L.D.

1029
01:08:07,617 --> 01:08:11,318
Is using the Tesseract
to build weapons of mass destruction.

1030
01:08:11,955 --> 01:08:13,069
Because of him.

1031
01:08:14,374 --> 01:08:15,370
Me?

1032
01:08:16,334 --> 01:08:18,707
Last year, Earth had a visitor
from another planet

1033
01:08:18,838 --> 01:08:22,004
who had a grudge match
that levelled a small town.

1034
01:08:22,133 --> 01:08:24,339
We learned that
not only are we not alone

1035
01:08:24,468 --> 01:08:28,051
but we are hopelessly,
hilariously, outgunned.

1036
01:08:28,180 --> 01:08:30,422
My people want nothing
but peace with your planet.

1037
01:08:30,558 --> 01:08:32,515
But you're not the only people
out there, are you?

1038
01:08:32,643 --> 01:08:34,600
And you're not the only threat.

1039
01:08:34,728 --> 01:08:37,896
The world's filling up with
people who can't be matched,

1040
01:08:38,567 --> 01:08:39,765
that can't be controlled.

1041
01:08:39,901 --> 01:08:41,016
Like you controlled the Cube?

1042
01:08:41,153 --> 01:08:42,398
Your work with the Tesseract

1043
01:08:42,529 --> 01:08:45,102
is what drew Loki to it, and his allies.

1044
01:08:45,240 --> 01:08:46,615
It is a signal to all the realms

1045
01:08:46,742 --> 01:08:49,411
that the Earth is ready
for a higher form of war.

1046
01:08:49,536 --> 01:08:50,615
A higher form?

1047
01:08:50,746 --> 01:08:51,741
You forced our hand.

1048
01:08:51,872 --> 01:08:52,867
We had to come up with something.

1049
01:08:52,998 --> 01:08:53,994
A nuclear deterrent.

1050
01:08:54,124 --> 01:08:56,117
Because that always
calms everything right down.

1051
01:08:56,251 --> 01:08:58,624
Remind me again how
you made your fortune, Stark.

1052
01:08:58,755 --> 01:09:01,127
I'm sure if he still made weapons,
Stark would be neck-deep...

1053
01:09:01,257 --> 01:09:02,882
Hold on. How is this now about me?

1054
01:09:03,009 --> 01:09:04,123
I'm sorry, isn't everything?

1055
01:09:04,260 --> 01:09:06,134
I thought humans were
more evolved than this.

1056
01:09:06,262 --> 01:09:09,133
Excuse me, did we come to
your planet and blow stuff up?

1057
01:09:09,265 --> 01:09:11,139
You treat your champions
with such mistrust.

1058
01:09:11,267 --> 01:09:12,726
Are you boys really that naïve?

1059
01:09:12,852 --> 01:09:14,726
S.H.I.E.L.D. monitors potential threats.

1060
01:09:14,854 --> 01:09:16,134
Captain America's on threat watch?

1061
01:09:16,272 --> 01:09:17,268
We all are.

1062
01:09:17,398 --> 01:09:18,810
Wait, you're on that list?

1063
01:09:18,942 --> 01:09:20,485
Are you above or below angry bees?

1064
01:09:20,611 --> 01:09:22,734
Stark, so help me God,
if you make one more wisecrack...

1065
01:09:22,863 --> 01:09:24,108
Threat! Verbal threat. I feel threatened.

1066
01:09:24,239 --> 01:09:26,730
- Show some respect.
- Respect what?

1067
01:09:34,083 --> 01:09:37,000
<i>Transport Six-Six-Bravo,
please relay confirm codes.</i>

1068
01:09:37,127 --> 01:09:39,287
<i>I've got you on the computer,
but not on the day log.</i>

1069
01:09:39,422 --> 01:09:41,498
<i>What is your haul? Over.</i>

1070
01:09:41,633 --> 01:09:44,254
<i>Arms and ammunition. Over.</i>

1071
01:09:52,602 --> 01:09:54,809
You speak of control,
yet you court chaos.

1072
01:09:54,938 --> 01:09:56,646
That's his M.O., isn't it?

1073
01:09:56,773 --> 01:09:58,018
I mean, what are we, a team?

1074
01:09:58,149 --> 01:10:01,104
No, we're a chemical mixture
that makes chaos.

1075
01:10:01,237 --> 01:10:03,194
We're a time bomb.

1076
01:10:03,322 --> 01:10:05,149
You need to step away.

1077
01:10:05,283 --> 01:10:07,109
Why shouldn't the guy
let off a little steam?

1078
01:10:07,243 --> 01:10:09,366
You know damn well why. Back off!

1079
01:10:09,495 --> 01:10:11,701
I'm starting to want you to make me.

1080
01:10:11,831 --> 01:10:15,449
Yeah. Big man in a suit of armour.

1081
01:10:15,585 --> 01:10:17,043
Take that off, what are you?

1082
01:10:17,169 --> 01:10:19,496
Genius, billionaire,
playboy, philanthropist.

1083
01:10:20,382 --> 01:10:23,549
I know guys with none of that
worth ten of you.

1084
01:10:23,677 --> 01:10:24,673
I've seen the footage.

1085
01:10:24,803 --> 01:10:27,045
The only thing you really
fight for is yourself.

1086
01:10:28,515 --> 01:10:30,424
You're not the guy
to make the sacrifice play,

1087
01:10:30,559 --> 01:10:33,050
to lay down on a wire and let
the other guy crawl over you.

1088
01:10:33,187 --> 01:10:35,309
I think I would just cut the wire.

1089
01:10:37,941 --> 01:10:40,149
Always a way out.

1090
01:10:40,278 --> 01:10:41,523
You may not be a threat

1091
01:10:41,654 --> 01:10:43,564
but you better stop pretending
to be a hero.

1092
01:10:43,698 --> 01:10:46,154
A hero? Like you?

1093
01:10:46,284 --> 01:10:48,324
You're a laboratory experiment, Rogers.

1094
01:10:48,453 --> 01:10:52,071
Everything special about you
came out of a bottle.

1095
01:11:17,358 --> 01:11:20,194
Put on the suit. Let's go a few rounds.

1096
01:11:21,196 --> 01:11:24,647
You people are so petty and tiny.

1097
01:11:24,783 --> 01:11:25,779
Yeah, this is a team.

1098
01:11:25,909 --> 01:11:27,154
Agent Romanoff, would you escort

1099
01:11:27,285 --> 01:11:28,400
Dr Banner back to his...

1100
01:11:28,537 --> 01:11:30,197
Where? You rented my room.

1101
01:11:30,330 --> 01:11:31,789
The cell was just in case...

1102
01:11:31,915 --> 01:11:33,457
In case you needed to kill me.

1103
01:11:33,583 --> 01:11:36,501
But you can't. I know, I tried.

1104
01:11:39,214 --> 01:11:42,133
I got low. I didn't see an end.

1105
01:11:42,260 --> 01:11:46,720
So, I put a bullet in my mouth,
and the other guy spit it out.

1106
01:11:47,306 --> 01:11:48,505
So I moved on.

1107
01:11:48,641 --> 01:11:51,476
I focused on helping
other people. I was good.

1108
01:11:51,602 --> 01:11:53,809
Until you dragged me back
into this freak show

1109
01:11:53,938 --> 01:11:55,313
and put everyone here at risk.

1110
01:11:55,440 --> 01:11:57,516
You want to know my secret,
Agent Romanoff?

1111
01:11:57,650 --> 01:11:59,477
You want to know how I stay calm?

1112
01:12:02,281 --> 01:12:04,439
Dr Banner,

1113
01:12:05,242 --> 01:12:06,571
put down the sceptre.

1114
01:12:15,336 --> 01:12:16,498
Got it.

1115
01:12:17,338 --> 01:12:18,333
Sorry, kids,

1116
01:12:18,464 --> 01:12:20,207
you don't get to see
my party trick after all.

1117
01:12:20,341 --> 01:12:21,337
You located the Tesseract?

1118
01:12:21,468 --> 01:12:22,463
I could get there fastest.

1119
01:12:22,594 --> 01:12:24,717
The Tesseract belongs on Asgard.
No human is a match for it.

1120
01:12:24,846 --> 01:12:26,174
- You're not going alone.
- You're gonna stop me?

1121
01:12:26,306 --> 01:12:27,302
Put on the suit, let's find out.

1122
01:12:27,432 --> 01:12:28,712
I'm not afraid to hit an old man.

1123
01:12:28,850 --> 01:12:29,846
Put on the suit.

1124
01:12:32,729 --> 01:12:34,354
Oh, my God.

1125
01:12:49,872 --> 01:12:50,868
Put on the suit.

1126
01:12:50,998 --> 01:12:52,279
Yeah.

1127
01:12:55,044 --> 01:12:56,787
<i>All hands to stations.</i>

1128
01:13:00,925 --> 01:13:02,717
<i>- Hill!
- External detonation.</i>

1129
01:13:02,845 --> 01:13:04,089
Number three engine is down.

1130
01:13:04,221 --> 01:13:05,217
We've been hit.

1131
01:13:05,347 --> 01:13:06,510
- Can they get it running?
- Fire in engine three!

1132
01:13:06,640 --> 01:13:07,636
Talk to me.

1133
01:13:07,766 --> 01:13:09,391
Turbine looks mostly intact

1134
01:13:09,518 --> 01:13:11,392
but it's impossible to
get out there to make repairs

1135
01:13:11,520 --> 01:13:12,931
while we're in the air.

1136
01:13:13,063 --> 01:13:15,601
If we lose one more engine,
we won't be.

1137
01:13:15,732 --> 01:13:17,725
Somebody's got to get outside
and patch that engine.

1138
01:13:17,860 --> 01:13:19,567
<i>- Stark, you copy that?
- I'm on it.</i>

1139
01:13:19,695 --> 01:13:22,981
<i>Coulson, initiate defensive lockdown
in the detention section</i>

1140
01:13:23,116 --> 01:13:24,112
<i>then get to the armoury.</i>

1141
01:13:24,242 --> 01:13:25,357
Romanoff?

1142
01:13:28,997 --> 01:13:30,455
We're okay.

1143
01:13:33,042 --> 01:13:34,287
We're okay, right?

1144
01:13:46,891 --> 01:13:48,089
- Keep that engine down!
- Yes, sir.

1145
01:13:48,225 --> 01:13:49,933
Detention, wait for cameras to go dark.

1146
01:13:50,060 --> 01:13:51,852
- Got it.
- Stay close.

1147
01:13:53,606 --> 01:13:55,100
Let's go, Level 4.

1148
01:13:56,066 --> 01:13:58,854
Engine three. I'll meet you there.

1149
01:14:07,037 --> 01:14:08,199
Doctor?

1150
01:14:10,582 --> 01:14:11,578
Bruce?

1151
01:14:11,875 --> 01:14:15,540
You got to fight it.
This is just what Loki wants.

1152
01:14:16,922 --> 01:14:17,953
We're going to be okay. Listen to me.

1153
01:14:18,090 --> 01:14:19,085
Are you hurt?

1154
01:14:22,387 --> 01:14:24,593
We're going to be okay. All right?

1155
01:14:24,722 --> 01:14:27,474
I swear on my life,
I will get you out of this.

1156
01:14:27,600 --> 01:14:28,975
You will walk away and never ever...

1157
01:14:29,102 --> 01:14:31,178
Your life?

1158
01:14:47,705 --> 01:14:48,700
Bruce.

1159
01:15:25,578 --> 01:15:28,736
Bring the carrier about
to a 1-8-0, heading south!

1160
01:15:28,873 --> 01:15:30,747
- Take us to the water!
- We're flying blind.

1161
01:15:30,875 --> 01:15:32,867
Navigation's recalibrating
after the engine failure.

1162
01:15:33,002 --> 01:15:34,745
Is the sun coming up?

1163
01:15:35,504 --> 01:15:37,711
- Yes, sir.
- Then put it on the left.

1164
01:15:37,840 --> 01:15:39,500
Get us over water.

1165
01:15:39,634 --> 01:15:41,710
One more turbine goes down,
and we drop.

1166
01:15:43,972 --> 01:15:45,253
Thanks.

1167
01:15:48,602 --> 01:15:49,765
Stark!

1168
01:15:52,481 --> 01:15:54,141
Stark, I'm here!

1169
01:15:54,274 --> 01:15:55,768
<i>Good.</i>

1170
01:15:56,985 --> 01:15:58,978
<i>Let's see what we've got.</i>

1171
01:15:59,112 --> 01:16:00,772
I got to get this
superconducting coolant system

1172
01:16:00,906 --> 01:16:01,902
back online

1173
01:16:02,032 --> 01:16:03,491
before I can access the rotors,

1174
01:16:03,618 --> 01:16:05,445
work on dislodging the debris.

1175
01:16:07,997 --> 01:16:09,540
<i>I need you to get to that
engine control panel</i>

1176
01:16:09,666 --> 01:16:13,331
<i>and tell me which relays
are in overload position.</i>

1177
01:16:25,641 --> 01:16:27,183
<i>What does it look like in there?</i>

1178
01:16:27,893 --> 01:16:30,431
It seems to run
on some form of electricity.

1179
01:16:30,563 --> 01:16:32,306
Well, you're not wrong.

1180
01:17:36,131 --> 01:17:38,966
We are not your enemies, Banner.

1181
01:17:39,093 --> 01:17:40,088
Try to think!

1182
01:17:50,230 --> 01:17:52,104
<i>Okay, the relays are intact.</i>

1183
01:17:52,232 --> 01:17:53,691
What's our next move?

1184
01:17:53,817 --> 01:17:54,813
<i>Even if I clear the rotors,</i>

1185
01:17:54,943 --> 01:17:57,149
<i>this thing won't
re-engage without a jump.</i>

1186
01:17:57,279 --> 01:17:58,654
I'm going to have to
get in there and push.

1187
01:17:58,780 --> 01:18:00,523
If that thing gets up to
speed, you'll get shredded.

1188
01:18:00,657 --> 01:18:02,650
That stator control unit
can reverse the polarity

1189
01:18:02,784 --> 01:18:04,195
long enough to disengage
maglev and that could...

1190
01:18:04,327 --> 01:18:05,657
Speak English!

1191
01:18:06,998 --> 01:18:08,112
You see that red lever?

1192
01:18:09,417 --> 01:18:11,540
<i>It will slow the rotors down
long enough for me to get out.</i>

1193
01:18:11,669 --> 01:18:13,460
Stand by it. Wait for my word.

1194
01:19:06,059 --> 01:19:07,851
We need full evac
on the lower hangar bay.

1195
01:19:11,065 --> 01:19:12,096
Grenade!

1196
01:19:27,249 --> 01:19:28,577
<i>We've got a perimeter breach!</i>

1197
01:19:28,708 --> 01:19:30,748
<i>Hostiles are in S.H.I.E.L.D. gear.</i>

1198
01:19:30,877 --> 01:19:32,953
<i>Call-outs at every junction.</i>

1199
01:19:40,262 --> 01:19:42,468
<i>We have the Hulk and Thor
on Research Level 4.</i>

1200
01:19:42,597 --> 01:19:44,140
<i>Levels 2 and 3 are dark.</i>

1201
01:19:44,266 --> 01:19:46,389
Sir, the Hulk will tear this place apart!

1202
01:19:47,603 --> 01:19:48,599
Get his attention.

1203
01:19:48,730 --> 01:19:52,893
Escort 6-0, proceed to
Wishbone and engage hostile.

1204
01:19:53,026 --> 01:19:54,306
<i>Don't get too close.</i>

1205
01:19:54,444 --> 01:19:55,819
<i>Copy.</i>

1206
01:20:07,750 --> 01:20:09,125
<i>Target acquired.</i>

1207
01:20:13,422 --> 01:20:14,418
<i>Target engaged.</i>

1208
01:20:26,060 --> 01:20:27,603
<i>Target angry, target angry!</i>

1209
01:21:36,009 --> 01:21:38,215
They're not getting through
here, so what the hell...

1210
01:21:56,614 --> 01:21:58,856
<i>Engine one is now in shut-down.</i>

1211
01:22:07,291 --> 01:22:09,450
We are in an uncontrolled descent.

1212
01:22:09,586 --> 01:22:11,460
<i>Sir, we've lost all power in engine one.</i>

1213
01:22:12,005 --> 01:22:13,832
<i>It's Barton. He took out our systems.</i>

1214
01:22:13,965 --> 01:22:16,456
<i>He's headed for the detention level.</i>

1215
01:22:16,593 --> 01:22:18,550
<i>Does anybody copy?</i>

1216
01:22:19,721 --> 01:22:21,844
This is Agent Romanoff.

1217
01:22:21,973 --> 01:22:23,432
I copy.

1218
01:22:28,063 --> 01:22:29,059
<i>Stark, we're losing altitude.</i>

1219
01:22:29,190 --> 01:22:30,649
Yeah, I noticed.

1220
01:22:59,680 --> 01:23:00,711
No!

1221
01:23:08,314 --> 01:23:11,019
Are you ever not going to fall for that?

1222
01:23:54,029 --> 01:23:56,271
The humans think us immortal.

1223
01:23:57,366 --> 01:23:58,908
Should we test that?

1224
01:24:01,703 --> 01:24:02,901
Move away, please.

1225
01:24:07,376 --> 01:24:08,870
You like this?

1226
01:24:09,836 --> 01:24:13,088
We started working on the prototype
after you sent the Destroyer.

1227
01:24:14,300 --> 01:24:16,542
Even I don't know what it does.

1228
01:24:17,345 --> 01:24:18,590
Do you want to find out?

1229
01:24:20,598 --> 01:24:22,057
No!

1230
01:25:31,589 --> 01:25:33,001
Natasha?

1231
01:26:04,582 --> 01:26:06,326
You're going to lose.

1232
01:26:08,378 --> 01:26:09,576
Am I?

1233
01:26:10,880 --> 01:26:13,373
It's in your nature.

1234
01:26:15,553 --> 01:26:17,878
Your heroes are scattered.

1235
01:26:18,014 --> 01:26:21,714
Your floating fortress falls from the sky.

1236
01:26:21,851 --> 01:26:23,475
Where is my disadvantage?

1237
01:26:24,145 --> 01:26:26,221
You lack conviction.

1238
01:26:27,064 --> 01:26:28,060
I don't think I'm...

1239
01:26:34,907 --> 01:26:36,617
So, that's what it does.

1240
01:26:38,702 --> 01:26:41,822
<i>All hands
to crash stations immediately.</i>

1241
01:27:09,442 --> 01:27:10,438
Cap, hit the lever.

1242
01:27:10,819 --> 01:27:13,393
I need a minute here!

1243
01:27:13,531 --> 01:27:14,610
Lever

1244
01:27:14,740 --> 01:27:15,855
now!

1245
01:27:27,837 --> 01:27:28,951
<i>Help!</i>

1246
01:28:04,584 --> 01:28:05,959
Sorry, boss.

1247
01:28:06,085 --> 01:28:07,793
The god rabbited.

1248
01:28:07,920 --> 01:28:09,379
Just stay awake.

1249
01:28:09,505 --> 01:28:11,130
Eyes on me.

1250
01:28:11,257 --> 01:28:12,799
No, I'm clocking out here.

1251
01:28:12,925 --> 01:28:14,421
Not an option.

1252
01:28:15,429 --> 01:28:17,386
It's okay, boss.

1253
01:28:19,308 --> 01:28:21,347
This was never gonna work

1254
01:28:21,477 --> 01:28:22,757
if they didn't have something

1255
01:28:24,104 --> 01:28:25,646
to...

1256
01:28:54,762 --> 01:28:56,589
<i>Agent Coulson is down.</i>

1257
01:28:57,974 --> 01:28:59,682
<i>A medical team is on
its way to your location.</i>

1258
01:28:59,809 --> 01:29:01,268
<i>They're here.</i>

1259
01:29:04,480 --> 01:29:06,105
<i>They called it.</i>

1260
01:29:22,583 --> 01:29:24,207
These were in Phil Coulson's jacket.

1261
01:29:27,546 --> 01:29:29,669
I guess he never did
get you to sign them.

1262
01:29:33,177 --> 01:29:34,836
We're dead in the air up here.

1263
01:29:34,970 --> 01:29:38,055
Our communications,
the location of the Cube,

1264
01:29:38,183 --> 01:29:40,590
Banner, Thor...

1265
01:29:41,895 --> 01:29:43,804
I got nothing for you.

1266
01:29:43,938 --> 01:29:46,856
I lost my one good eye.

1267
01:29:49,903 --> 01:29:52,904
Maybe I had that coming.

1268
01:29:57,119 --> 01:29:58,400
Yes,

1269
01:29:59,580 --> 01:30:02,914
we were going to build
an arsenal with the Tesseract.

1270
01:30:04,376 --> 01:30:06,286
I never put all my chips
on that number, though

1271
01:30:06,420 --> 01:30:09,457
because I was playing
something even riskier.

1272
01:30:13,427 --> 01:30:17,556
There was an idea, Stark knows this,

1273
01:30:19,434 --> 01:30:22,768
called the Avengers Initiative.

1274
01:30:23,980 --> 01:30:26,103
The idea was to bring together a group

1275
01:30:26,233 --> 01:30:28,771
of remarkable people

1276
01:30:29,569 --> 01:30:32,404
to see if they could become
something more.

1277
01:30:33,782 --> 01:30:37,946
To see if they could work together
when we needed them to,

1278
01:30:38,079 --> 01:30:41,412
to fight the battles that we never could.

1279
01:30:44,168 --> 01:30:48,996
Phil Coulson died
still believing in that idea.

1280
01:30:51,342 --> 01:30:53,002
In heroes.

1281
01:31:01,103 --> 01:31:02,645
Well,

1282
01:31:03,522 --> 01:31:06,191
it's an old-fashioned notion.

1283
01:31:26,504 --> 01:31:28,995
<i>You fell out of the sky.</i>

1284
01:31:43,022 --> 01:31:44,516
Did I hurt anybody?

1285
01:31:44,649 --> 01:31:47,685
There's nobody around here to get hurt.

1286
01:31:47,818 --> 01:31:51,104
You did scare the hell
out of some pigeons, though.

1287
01:31:51,948 --> 01:31:52,979
Lucky.

1288
01:31:53,115 --> 01:31:54,740
Or just good aim.

1289
01:31:54,867 --> 01:31:56,445
You were awake when you fell.

1290
01:31:58,539 --> 01:32:00,578
- You saw?
- The whole thing.

1291
01:32:00,707 --> 01:32:02,332
Right through the ceiling.

1292
01:32:02,459 --> 01:32:06,409
Big and green and buck-ass nude.

1293
01:32:06,547 --> 01:32:07,661
Here.

1294
01:32:09,049 --> 01:32:11,207
Didn't think those would
fit you until you shrunk down

1295
01:32:11,343 --> 01:32:13,751
to a regular-size feller.

1296
01:32:16,098 --> 01:32:17,378
Thank you.

1297
01:32:18,393 --> 01:32:19,638
Are you an alien?

1298
01:32:20,228 --> 01:32:21,426
What?

1299
01:32:21,729 --> 01:32:23,058
From outer space, an alien.

1300
01:32:23,690 --> 01:32:24,686
No.

1301
01:32:25,066 --> 01:32:28,186
Well, then, son, you've got a condition.

1302
01:32:39,039 --> 01:32:41,365
Clint. You're going to be all right.

1303
01:32:44,712 --> 01:32:46,788
You know that?

1304
01:32:47,631 --> 01:32:49,505
Is that what you know?

1305
01:32:51,969 --> 01:32:54,840
I've got no window.

1306
01:32:55,639 --> 01:32:57,016
I have to flush him out.

1307
01:32:57,933 --> 01:32:59,761
You got to level out.
It's going to take time.

1308
01:32:59,895 --> 01:33:01,437
You don't understand.

1309
01:33:03,398 --> 01:33:06,648
Have you ever had someone
take your brain and play?

1310
01:33:07,444 --> 01:33:11,607
Pull you out
and stuff something else in?

1311
01:33:14,785 --> 01:33:17,157
Do you know what it's like
to be unmade?

1312
01:33:18,706 --> 01:33:21,078
You know that I do.

1313
01:33:28,674 --> 01:33:29,706
Why am I back?

1314
01:33:30,843 --> 01:33:32,219
How did you get him out?

1315
01:33:32,345 --> 01:33:35,180
Cognitive recalibration.

1316
01:33:35,306 --> 01:33:38,011
I hit you really hard on the head.

1317
01:33:38,142 --> 01:33:39,223
Thanks.

1318
01:33:43,524 --> 01:33:45,267
Natasha...

1319
01:33:45,943 --> 01:33:47,022
How many agents did I...

1320
01:33:47,152 --> 01:33:48,611
Don't.

1321
01:33:48,737 --> 01:33:50,944
Don't do that to yourself, Clint.

1322
01:33:51,532 --> 01:33:53,240
This is Loki.

1323
01:33:53,367 --> 01:33:55,988
This is monsters and magic,

1324
01:33:56,120 --> 01:33:57,744
and nothing we were ever trained for.

1325
01:33:57,871 --> 01:33:59,415
Loki, did he get away?

1326
01:33:59,541 --> 01:34:00,537
Yeah.

1327
01:34:00,875 --> 01:34:03,117
I don't suppose you know where.

1328
01:34:03,253 --> 01:34:05,044
I didn't need to know.

1329
01:34:05,171 --> 01:34:06,915
I didn't ask.

1330
01:34:10,176 --> 01:34:12,667
He's going to
make his play soon, though.

1331
01:34:13,013 --> 01:34:14,008
Today.

1332
01:34:14,139 --> 01:34:15,467
We got to stop him.

1333
01:34:16,141 --> 01:34:17,386
Yeah? Who's "we"?

1334
01:34:17,517 --> 01:34:19,475
I don't know. Whoever's left.

1335
01:34:20,688 --> 01:34:22,016
Well,

1336
01:34:23,733 --> 01:34:25,891
if I put an arrow
through Loki's eye socket,

1337
01:34:26,027 --> 01:34:28,731
I would sleep better, I suppose.

1338
01:34:31,574 --> 01:34:33,151
Now you sound like you.

1339
01:34:33,868 --> 01:34:35,327
But you don't.

1340
01:34:37,246 --> 01:34:40,082
You're a spy, not a soldier.

1341
01:34:40,209 --> 01:34:44,954
Now you want to wade into a war. Why?

1342
01:34:46,715 --> 01:34:48,672
What did Loki do to you?

1343
01:34:49,426 --> 01:34:51,834
He didn't. I just...

1344
01:34:55,599 --> 01:34:57,141
Natasha.

1345
01:34:59,228 --> 01:35:01,221
I've been compromised.

1346
01:35:04,317 --> 01:35:06,440
I got red in my ledger.

1347
01:35:08,571 --> 01:35:10,647
I would like to wipe it out.

1348
01:35:26,674 --> 01:35:28,168
Was he married?

1349
01:35:28,300 --> 01:35:29,711
No.

1350
01:35:29,844 --> 01:35:34,055
There was a cellist, I think.

1351
01:35:35,641 --> 01:35:37,052
I'm sorry.

1352
01:35:37,768 --> 01:35:39,428
He seemed like a good man.

1353
01:35:40,731 --> 01:35:41,810
He was an idiot.

1354
01:35:41,940 --> 01:35:44,182
Why? For believing?

1355
01:35:44,317 --> 01:35:45,728
For taking on Loki alone.

1356
01:35:45,861 --> 01:35:47,569
He was doing his job.

1357
01:35:47,696 --> 01:35:50,234
He was out of his league.
He should have waited.

1358
01:35:50,365 --> 01:35:51,396
He should have...

1359
01:35:51,533 --> 01:35:53,111
Sometimes there isn't a way out, Tony.

1360
01:35:53,243 --> 01:35:55,366
Right, I've heard that before.

1361
01:35:55,495 --> 01:35:56,989
Is this the first time you lost a soldier?

1362
01:35:57,122 --> 01:35:58,913
We are not soldiers.

1363
01:36:03,379 --> 01:36:05,123
I'm not marching to Fury's fife.

1364
01:36:05,256 --> 01:36:06,419
Neither am I.

1365
01:36:06,549 --> 01:36:08,755
He's got the same blood
on his hands that Loki does.

1366
01:36:08,885 --> 01:36:10,260
But right now,
we got to put that behind us

1367
01:36:10,386 --> 01:36:12,593
and get this done.

1368
01:36:12,722 --> 01:36:13,718
Loki needs a power source.

1369
01:36:13,848 --> 01:36:14,844
If we can put together a list...

1370
01:36:14,974 --> 01:36:15,970
He made it personal.

1371
01:36:16,142 --> 01:36:17,173
That's not the point.

1372
01:36:17,310 --> 01:36:19,682
That is the point. That's Loki's point.

1373
01:36:19,812 --> 01:36:21,723
He hit us all right where we live. Why?

1374
01:36:21,857 --> 01:36:22,853
To tear us apart.

1375
01:36:22,983 --> 01:36:24,857
Yeah, divide and conquer is great

1376
01:36:24,985 --> 01:36:27,441
but he knows he has to
take us out to win, right?

1377
01:36:27,571 --> 01:36:29,113
That's what he wants.

1378
01:36:29,239 --> 01:36:31,730
He wants to beat us,
he wants to be seen doing it.

1379
01:36:31,867 --> 01:36:32,982
He wants an audience.

1380
01:36:33,702 --> 01:36:35,362
Right. I caught his act in Stuttgart.

1381
01:36:35,496 --> 01:36:38,413
Yeah, that was just previews.
This is opening night.

1382
01:36:38,540 --> 01:36:41,078
And Loki, he's a full-tilt diva, right?

1383
01:36:41,210 --> 01:36:42,788
He wants flowers, he wants parades.

1384
01:36:42,921 --> 01:36:46,705
He wants a monument built to the skies
with his name plastered...

1385
01:36:48,468 --> 01:36:50,046
Son of a bitch.

1386
01:37:01,314 --> 01:37:02,347
Time to go.

1387
01:37:02,483 --> 01:37:04,025
- Go where?
- I'll tell you on the way.

1388
01:37:04,151 --> 01:37:05,147
Can you fly one of those jets?

1389
01:37:06,737 --> 01:37:07,982
I can.

1390
01:37:11,867 --> 01:37:12,899
You got a suit?

1391
01:37:13,035 --> 01:37:14,031
Yeah.

1392
01:37:14,161 --> 01:37:15,620
Then suit up.

1393
01:37:43,276 --> 01:37:44,556
Hey, you guys aren't
authorised to be in here.

1394
01:37:44,694 --> 01:37:47,019
Son, just don't.

1395
01:37:49,073 --> 01:37:50,069
Sir.

1396
01:37:50,200 --> 01:37:51,398
Agent Hill.

1397
01:37:51,951 --> 01:37:53,493
Those cards,

1398
01:37:55,622 --> 01:38:00,082
they were in Coulson's locker,
not in his jacket.

1399
01:38:04,507 --> 01:38:06,084
They needed the push.

1400
01:38:09,178 --> 01:38:11,467
<i>We have an unauthorised departure
from Bay 6.</i>

1401
01:38:12,348 --> 01:38:13,676
They found him.

1402
01:38:14,517 --> 01:38:18,217
Get our communications back up,
whatever you have to do.

1403
01:38:18,354 --> 01:38:20,596
- I want eyes on everything.
- Yes, sir.

1404
01:38:34,162 --> 01:38:35,906
<i>Sir, I've turned off the arc reactor</i>

1405
01:38:36,039 --> 01:38:39,871
<i>but the device
is already self-sustaining.</i>

1406
01:38:40,001 --> 01:38:42,160
<i>Shut it down, Dr Selvig.</i>

1407
01:38:42,838 --> 01:38:44,119
It's too late!

1408
01:38:46,175 --> 01:38:47,634
She can't stop now.

1409
01:38:48,678 --> 01:38:51,133
She wants to show us something!

1410
01:38:51,264 --> 01:38:53,303
A new universe.

1411
01:38:53,433 --> 01:38:54,975
<i>Okay.</i>

1412
01:39:02,025 --> 01:39:03,899
<i>The barrier is pure energy.</i>

1413
01:39:04,028 --> 01:39:05,901
<i>It's unbreachable.</i>

1414
01:39:06,030 --> 01:39:07,821
<i>Yeah, I got that.</i>

1415
01:39:09,033 --> 01:39:10,028
<i>Plan B.</i>

1416
01:39:11,201 --> 01:39:13,277
<i>Sir, the Mark 7
is not ready for deployment.</i>

1417
01:39:13,412 --> 01:39:15,654
Then skip the spinning rims.
We're on the clock.

1418
01:39:35,393 --> 01:39:38,430
Please tell me you're going
to appeal to my humanity.

1419
01:39:39,564 --> 01:39:41,936
Actually, I'm planning to threaten you.

1420
01:39:42,067 --> 01:39:43,525
You should have left
your armour on for that.

1421
01:39:43,652 --> 01:39:45,063
Yeah.

1422
01:39:45,196 --> 01:39:46,275
It's seen a bit of mileage,

1423
01:39:46,405 --> 01:39:49,027
and you've got
the glow stick of destiny.

1424
01:39:49,825 --> 01:39:52,114
Would you like a drink?

1425
01:39:52,245 --> 01:39:53,359
Stalling me won't change anything.

1426
01:39:53,496 --> 01:39:55,619
No, no. Threatening.

1427
01:39:55,748 --> 01:39:57,123
No drink? Are you sure?

1428
01:39:57,250 --> 01:39:58,792
I'm having one.

1429
01:39:59,835 --> 01:40:03,750
The Chitauri are coming.
Nothing will change that.

1430
01:40:04,633 --> 01:40:06,044
What have I to fear?

1431
01:40:06,176 --> 01:40:07,884
The Avengers.

1432
01:40:09,972 --> 01:40:12,297
That's what we call ourselves.
We're sort of like a team.

1433
01:40:12,432 --> 01:40:14,057
"Earth's mightiest heroes"- type thing.

1434
01:40:14,184 --> 01:40:16,058
Yes, I've met them.

1435
01:40:16,186 --> 01:40:17,217
Yeah.

1436
01:40:17,354 --> 01:40:18,517
It takes us a while to get any traction,

1437
01:40:18,647 --> 01:40:19,643
I'll give you that one.

1438
01:40:19,773 --> 01:40:21,979
But let's do a head count, here.

1439
01:40:22,109 --> 01:40:24,600
Your brother, the demigod,

1440
01:40:26,322 --> 01:40:29,905
a super soldier, a living legend
who kind of lives up to the legend.

1441
01:40:30,034 --> 01:40:33,201
A man with breathtaking
anger-management issues,

1442
01:40:33,329 --> 01:40:36,414
a couple of master assassins,
and you, big fella,

1443
01:40:37,041 --> 01:40:39,995
you've managed to piss off
every single one of them.

1444
01:40:40,128 --> 01:40:41,124
That was the plan.

1445
01:40:41,254 --> 01:40:43,247
Not a great plan.

1446
01:40:43,381 --> 01:40:45,422
When they come,

1447
01:40:45,551 --> 01:40:47,010
and they will,

1448
01:40:47,136 --> 01:40:48,381
they'll come for you.

1449
01:40:48,512 --> 01:40:49,508
I have an army.

1450
01:40:49,638 --> 01:40:50,801
We have a Hulk.

1451
01:40:51,307 --> 01:40:52,682
I thought the beast had wandered off.

1452
01:40:52,808 --> 01:40:54,717
You're missing the point.
There is no throne.

1453
01:40:54,852 --> 01:40:58,850
There is no version of this
where you come out on top.

1454
01:40:58,981 --> 01:41:01,306
Maybe your army comes
and maybe it's too much for us,

1455
01:41:01,442 --> 01:41:03,434
but it's all on you.

1456
01:41:04,236 --> 01:41:05,317
Because if we can't protect the Earth,

1457
01:41:05,489 --> 01:41:08,608
you can be damn well sure
we'll avenge it.

1458
01:41:10,660 --> 01:41:13,697
How will your friends have time for me

1459
01:41:13,830 --> 01:41:15,622
when they are so busy fighting you?

1460
01:41:23,048 --> 01:41:24,079
This usually works.

1461
01:41:24,216 --> 01:41:27,052
Well, performance issues,
it's not uncommon.

1462
01:41:27,178 --> 01:41:29,087
One out of five...

1463
01:41:30,556 --> 01:41:33,471
Jarvis, anytime now.

1464
01:41:35,228 --> 01:41:37,979
You will all fall before me.

1465
01:41:38,106 --> 01:41:39,481
Deploy!

1466
01:41:39,607 --> 01:41:41,018
Deploy!

1467
01:42:08,221 --> 01:42:11,175
<i>And there's one other
person you pissed off.</i>

1468
01:42:12,309 --> 01:42:13,554
<i>His name was Phil.</i>

1469
01:42:37,335 --> 01:42:38,829
Right.

1470
01:42:38,961 --> 01:42:40,206
Army.

1471
01:43:52,581 --> 01:43:53,861
Loki!

1472
01:43:53,999 --> 01:43:56,038
Turn off the Tesseract, or I'll destroy it.

1473
01:43:56,168 --> 01:43:57,199
You can't.

1474
01:43:57,335 --> 01:43:59,209
There is no stopping it.

1475
01:43:59,337 --> 01:44:01,129
There is only

1476
01:44:01,256 --> 01:44:02,371
the war.

1477
01:44:02,507 --> 01:44:03,622
So be it.

1478
01:44:25,740 --> 01:44:27,483
<i>Stark, we're on your three,
headed northeast.</i>

1479
01:44:27,617 --> 01:44:29,741
What? Did you stop for drive-through?

1480
01:44:29,870 --> 01:44:31,578
Swing up Park. I'm going
to lay them out for you.

1481
01:44:49,641 --> 01:44:50,969
<i>Sir, we have more incoming.</i>

1482
01:44:51,101 --> 01:44:52,844
Fine. Let's keep them occupied.

1483
01:44:59,734 --> 01:45:01,608
- Nat?
- I see him.

1484
01:45:45,949 --> 01:45:48,156
We got to get back up there.

1485
01:46:39,506 --> 01:46:41,166
Stark, are you seeing this?

1486
01:46:41,925 --> 01:46:44,381
<i>Seeing. Still working on believing.</i>

1487
01:46:44,511 --> 01:46:45,886
Where's Banner?
Has he shown up yet?

1488
01:46:46,012 --> 01:46:47,044
<i>Banner?</i>

1489
01:46:47,180 --> 01:46:48,212
Just keep me posted.

1490
01:46:48,932 --> 01:46:51,091
<i>Jarvis, find me a soft spot.</i>

1491
01:46:53,354 --> 01:46:55,228
Look at this!

1492
01:46:55,356 --> 01:46:56,352
Look around you!

1493
01:46:57,358 --> 01:47:01,226
You think this madness
will end with your rule?

1494
01:47:01,362 --> 01:47:02,856
It's too late.

1495
01:47:04,365 --> 01:47:05,610
It's too late to stop it.

1496
01:47:05,742 --> 01:47:09,609
No. We can, together.

1497
01:47:16,211 --> 01:47:18,334
Sentiment.

1498
01:47:45,909 --> 01:47:48,447
We've got civilians
still trapped up here.

1499
01:47:49,621 --> 01:47:50,617
Loki.

1500
01:48:02,260 --> 01:48:04,051
They're fish in a barrel down there.

1501
01:48:09,517 --> 01:48:11,475
We got this. It's good. Go.

1502
01:48:11,603 --> 01:48:12,979
Do you think you can hold them off?

1503
01:48:13,105 --> 01:48:14,101
Captain,

1504
01:48:16,108 --> 01:48:18,943
it would be my genuine pleasure.

1505
01:48:45,805 --> 01:48:47,513
Just like Budapest all over again.

1506
01:48:48,141 --> 01:48:50,632
You and I remember Budapest
very differently.

1507
01:49:06,786 --> 01:49:07,781
It's going to be an hour

1508
01:49:07,912 --> 01:49:09,192
before they can
scramble the National Guard.

1509
01:49:09,330 --> 01:49:11,121
National Guard?

1510
01:49:12,082 --> 01:49:13,578
Does the army know
what's happening here?

1511
01:49:13,835 --> 01:49:14,831
Do we?

1512
01:49:16,046 --> 01:49:17,244
You need men in these buildings.

1513
01:49:17,380 --> 01:49:18,875
There are people inside and
they're going to be running

1514
01:49:19,007 --> 01:49:20,205
right into the line of fire.

1515
01:49:20,342 --> 01:49:22,251
You take them to the basements
or through the subway.

1516
01:49:22,386 --> 01:49:23,963
You keep them off the streets.

1517
01:49:24,096 --> 01:49:26,717
I need a perimeter as far back as 39th.

1518
01:49:26,848 --> 01:49:28,473
Why the hell
should I take orders from you?

1519
01:49:42,532 --> 01:49:43,730
I need men in those buildings.

1520
01:49:43,866 --> 01:49:45,942
Lead the people down
and away from the streets.

1521
01:49:46,077 --> 01:49:48,650
We're going to set up a perimeter
all the way down to 39th Street.

1522
01:49:59,049 --> 01:50:00,627
Well, we got its attention.

1523
01:50:00,759 --> 01:50:02,633
<i>What the hell was step two?</i>

1524
01:50:32,167 --> 01:50:33,163
What's the story upstairs?

1525
01:50:33,293 --> 01:50:35,203
The power surrounding the Cube
is impenetrable.

1526
01:50:35,338 --> 01:50:37,959
<i>Thor's right. We got
to deal with these guys.</i>

1527
01:50:38,090 --> 01:50:39,715
- How do we do this?
- As a team.

1528
01:50:39,842 --> 01:50:41,123
I have unfinished business with Loki.

1529
01:50:41,677 --> 01:50:42,709
Yeah? Well, get in line.

1530
01:50:42,845 --> 01:50:43,841
Save it.

1531
01:50:43,971 --> 01:50:45,300
Loki's going to keep
this fight focused on us,

1532
01:50:45,431 --> 01:50:46,462
and that's what we need.

1533
01:50:46,599 --> 01:50:48,259
Without him,
these things could run wild.

1534
01:50:48,392 --> 01:50:51,346
We got Stark up top.
He's going to need us to...

1535
01:50:58,695 --> 01:51:02,479
So, this all seems horrible.

1536
01:51:02,950 --> 01:51:04,064
I've seen worse.

1537
01:51:04,618 --> 01:51:05,614
Sorry.

1538
01:51:05,744 --> 01:51:08,413
No, we could use a little worse.

1539
01:51:08,539 --> 01:51:10,946
<i>- Stark, we got him.
- Banner?</i>

1540
01:51:11,083 --> 01:51:12,328
Just like you said.

1541
01:51:12,459 --> 01:51:15,165
Then tell him to suit up.
I'm bringing the party to you.

1542
01:51:21,636 --> 01:51:23,712
I don't see how that's a party.

1543
01:51:31,563 --> 01:51:32,558
Dr Banner.

1544
01:51:34,316 --> 01:51:36,108
Now might be a really good
time for you to get angry.

1545
01:51:37,153 --> 01:51:39,608
That's my secret, Captain.

1546
01:51:41,323 --> 01:51:42,568
I'm always angry.

1547
01:51:54,044 --> 01:51:55,670
<i>Hold on!</i>

1548
01:52:25,578 --> 01:52:27,120
Send the rest.

1549
01:52:33,878 --> 01:52:35,124
Guys.

1550
01:52:35,255 --> 01:52:36,454
<i>Call it, Captain.</i>

1551
01:52:36,590 --> 01:52:37,753
All right, listen up.

1552
01:52:37,883 --> 01:52:40,670
Until we can close that portal,
our priority is containment.

1553
01:52:40,803 --> 01:52:42,131
Barton, I want you on that roof.

1554
01:52:42,262 --> 01:52:44,136
Eyes on everything.
Call out patterns and strays.

1555
01:52:44,264 --> 01:52:45,640
Stark, you got the perimeter.

1556
01:52:45,766 --> 01:52:46,929
Anything gets
more than three blocks out,

1557
01:52:47,059 --> 01:52:48,601
you turn it back or you turn it to ash.

1558
01:52:48,727 --> 01:52:49,925
<i>- Can you give me a lift?
- Right.</i>

1559
01:52:50,062 --> 01:52:51,141
<i>Better clench up, Legolas.</i>

1560
01:52:54,733 --> 01:52:57,106
Thor, you got to try
and bottleneck that portal.

1561
01:52:57,237 --> 01:52:58,399
Slow them down.

1562
01:52:58,530 --> 01:53:00,688
You got the lightning.
Light the bastards up.

1563
01:53:02,993 --> 01:53:04,617
You and me,
we stay here on the ground.

1564
01:53:04,744 --> 01:53:05,776
We keep the fighting here.

1565
01:53:05,912 --> 01:53:06,908
And Hulk...

1566
01:53:09,624 --> 01:53:10,703
Smash.

1567
01:54:04,307 --> 01:54:05,422
Sir.

1568
01:54:06,476 --> 01:54:07,472
The Council is on.

1569
01:54:12,357 --> 01:54:15,607
Stark, you got a lot of strays
sniffing your tail.

1570
01:54:17,446 --> 01:54:19,486
I'm just trying to keep them
off the streets.

1571
01:54:19,615 --> 01:54:21,857
Well, they can't bank worth a damn.

1572
01:54:21,992 --> 01:54:23,155
So find a tight corner.

1573
01:54:23,285 --> 01:54:24,614
I will roger that.

1574
01:54:47,602 --> 01:54:48,765
Oh, boy.

1575
01:54:55,777 --> 01:54:57,403
Nice call.

1576
01:54:57,530 --> 01:54:58,728
What else you got?

1577
01:54:58,865 --> 01:55:01,652
<i>Thor is taking on
a squadron down on Sixth.</i>

1578
01:55:01,784 --> 01:55:03,991
And he didn't invite me.

1579
01:55:43,495 --> 01:55:45,119
Captain, none of this
is going to mean a damn thing

1580
01:55:45,246 --> 01:55:46,491
if we don't close that portal.

1581
01:55:46,623 --> 01:55:48,283
Our biggest guns couldn't touch it.

1582
01:55:48,416 --> 01:55:50,658
Well, maybe it's not about guns.

1583
01:55:52,587 --> 01:55:54,544
If you want to get up there,
you're going to need a ride.

1584
01:55:55,632 --> 01:55:56,711
I got a ride.

1585
01:55:57,842 --> 01:55:58,875
I could use a boost, though.

1586
01:56:01,472 --> 01:56:02,468
Are you sure about this?

1587
01:56:02,932 --> 01:56:05,470
Yeah. It's gonna be fun.

1588
01:56:32,504 --> 01:56:34,378
Okay, turn, turn.

1589
01:56:34,506 --> 01:56:36,250
Less! Less!

1590
01:57:58,970 --> 01:58:01,925
<i>Captain, the bank
on 42nd past Madison.</i>

1591
01:58:02,057 --> 01:58:03,801
<i>They've cornered
a lot of civilians in there.</i>

1592
01:58:03,934 --> 01:58:05,843
I'm on it.

1593
01:58:25,957 --> 01:58:27,749
Everyone! Clear out!

1594
01:58:57,657 --> 01:58:59,317
<i>Director Fury,</i>

1595
01:58:59,450 --> 01:59:01,242
<i>the Council has made a decision.</i>

1596
01:59:01,370 --> 01:59:04,121
I recognise the Council
has made a decision.

1597
01:59:04,248 --> 01:59:05,825
But given that
it's a stupid-ass decision,

1598
01:59:05,958 --> 01:59:07,368
I have elected to ignore it.

1599
01:59:07,501 --> 01:59:10,834
<i>Director, you're closer
than any of our subs.</i>

1600
01:59:10,963 --> 01:59:11,958
<i>You scramble that jet...</i>

1601
01:59:12,089 --> 01:59:14,794
That is the island of Manhattan,
Councilman.

1602
01:59:14,925 --> 01:59:17,001
Until I'm certain my team can't hold it,

1603
01:59:17,135 --> 01:59:19,093
I will not order a nuclear strike

1604
01:59:19,263 --> 01:59:20,673
against a civilian population.

1605
01:59:20,806 --> 01:59:23,214
<i>If we don't hold them here,
we lose everything.</i>

1606
01:59:23,351 --> 01:59:26,103
If I send that bird out, we already have.

1607
01:59:29,858 --> 01:59:31,566
You.

1608
01:59:33,820 --> 01:59:34,982
Hawkeye!

1609
01:59:36,447 --> 01:59:37,443
Nat, what are you doing?

1610
01:59:38,366 --> 01:59:39,362
A little help?

1611
01:59:44,665 --> 01:59:45,661
I got him.

1612
02:00:12,235 --> 02:00:13,231
Enough!

1613
02:00:13,570 --> 02:00:16,026
You are, all of you, beneath me!

1614
02:00:16,156 --> 02:00:18,908
I am a god, you dull creature.

1615
02:00:19,034 --> 02:00:20,528
And I will not be bullied by...

1616
02:00:30,380 --> 02:00:32,253
Puny god.

1617
02:00:40,390 --> 02:00:41,848
The sceptre...

1618
02:00:43,018 --> 02:00:44,216
Doctor.

1619
02:00:46,105 --> 02:00:48,940
Loki's sceptre. The energy.

1620
02:00:49,066 --> 02:00:50,726
The Tesseract can't fight,

1621
02:00:50,859 --> 02:00:52,899
but you can't protect against yourself.

1622
02:00:53,028 --> 02:00:54,024
It's not your fault.

1623
02:00:54,154 --> 02:00:55,399
You didn't know what you were doing.

1624
02:00:58,450 --> 02:01:00,609
Actually, I think I did.

1625
02:01:00,744 --> 02:01:03,699
I built in a safety
to cut their power source.

1626
02:01:04,916 --> 02:01:06,327
Loki's sceptre.

1627
02:01:06,459 --> 02:01:09,033
It may be able to close the portal.

1628
02:01:11,131 --> 02:01:13,289
And I'm looking right at it.

1629
02:01:25,271 --> 02:01:29,138
<i>Sir, we will lose power
before we penetrate that shell.</i>

1630
02:01:35,781 --> 02:01:39,067
Jarvis, you ever hear the tale of Jonah?

1631
02:01:39,201 --> 02:01:41,574
<i>I wouldn't consider him a role model.</i>

1632
02:02:51,194 --> 02:02:52,986
<i>Director Fury is no longer in command.</i>

1633
02:02:53,113 --> 02:02:55,152
<i>Override order 7-Alpha- 1- 1.</i>

1634
02:02:55,282 --> 02:02:57,855
<i>7-Alpha-1-1, confirmed.
We're go for takeoff.</i>

1635
02:02:58,744 --> 02:03:00,820
Sir, we have a bird in motion!

1636
02:03:01,329 --> 02:03:03,322
Anyone on the deck,
we have a rogue bird.

1637
02:03:03,457 --> 02:03:04,738
We need to shut it down!

1638
02:03:04,876 --> 02:03:07,082
Repeat, takeoff is not authorised.

1639
02:03:37,618 --> 02:03:39,776
Stark, do you hear me?

1640
02:03:39,912 --> 02:03:42,035
You have a missile
headed straight for the city.

1641
02:03:42,581 --> 02:03:43,956
<i>How long?</i>

1642
02:03:44,083 --> 02:03:46,160
<i>Three minutes, max.</i>

1643
02:03:46,294 --> 02:03:47,919
<i>The payload will wipe out Midtown.</i>

1644
02:03:48,046 --> 02:03:50,085
Jarvis, put everything we got
into the thrusters.

1645
02:03:50,215 --> 02:03:51,875
<i>I just did.</i>

1646
02:04:04,771 --> 02:04:06,100
<i>Package is sent.</i>

1647
02:04:06,232 --> 02:04:09,352
<i>Detonation in
2 minutes, 30 seconds, mark.</i>

1648
02:04:32,134 --> 02:04:34,506
Are you ready for another bout?

1649
02:04:35,179 --> 02:04:36,210
What, are you getting sleepy?

1650
02:04:41,810 --> 02:04:43,554
Right at the crown!

1651
02:04:49,569 --> 02:04:51,360
I can close it.

1652
02:04:51,488 --> 02:04:53,527
Can anybody copy?

1653
02:04:53,656 --> 02:04:54,771
I can shut the portal down.

1654
02:04:54,908 --> 02:04:56,947
<i>- Do it!
- No, wait.</i>

1655
02:04:57,076 --> 02:04:58,321
Stark, these things are still coming.

1656
02:04:58,453 --> 02:04:59,449
I got a nuke coming in.

1657
02:04:59,579 --> 02:05:01,488
It's gonna blow in less than a minute.

1658
02:05:11,175 --> 02:05:13,002
And I know just where to put it.

1659
02:05:20,184 --> 02:05:22,556
<i>Stark, you know that's a one-way trip.</i>

1660
02:05:22,686 --> 02:05:24,062
Save the rest for the turn, J.

1661
02:05:24,188 --> 02:05:28,269
<i>Sir, shall I try Miss Potts?</i>

1662
02:05:28,402 --> 02:05:30,441
Might as well.

1663
02:05:32,364 --> 02:05:34,736
<i>The streets of New York City
have become a battleground.</i>

1664
02:05:34,866 --> 02:05:37,571
<i>The Army is here trying
to contain the violence</i>

1665
02:05:37,702 --> 02:05:39,161
<i>but clearly, it is outmatched.</i>

1666
02:05:39,287 --> 02:05:41,576
<i>And I have to say,
in all my years of reporting,</i>

1667
02:05:41,706 --> 02:05:44,624
<i>I have never seen anything like this.</i>

1668
02:05:44,751 --> 02:05:46,245
<i>We have limited information
on the team</i>

1669
02:05:46,378 --> 02:05:50,127
<i>but we do know that
billionaire Tony Stark's Iron Man...</i>

1670
02:07:03,459 --> 02:07:05,286
Come on, Stark.

1671
02:07:11,927 --> 02:07:13,042
Close it.

1672
02:07:33,116 --> 02:07:34,112
Son of a gun.

1673
02:07:38,872 --> 02:07:40,496
He's not slowing down.

1674
02:07:58,559 --> 02:08:00,018
Is he breathing?

1675
02:08:27,881 --> 02:08:29,293
What the hell?

1676
02:08:32,011 --> 02:08:34,134
What just happened?

1677
02:08:34,263 --> 02:08:36,552
Please tell me nobody kissed me.

1678
02:08:40,853 --> 02:08:42,513
We won.

1679
02:08:44,857 --> 02:08:46,138
All right, yay!

1680
02:08:46,275 --> 02:08:48,233
Hurray. Good job, guys.

1681
02:08:48,361 --> 02:08:51,565
Let's just not come in tomorrow.
Let's just take a day.

1682
02:08:52,449 --> 02:08:54,027
Have you ever tried shawarma?

1683
02:08:54,451 --> 02:08:56,740
There's a shawarma joint
about two blocks from here.

1684
02:08:56,870 --> 02:08:58,530
I don't know what it is,
but I want to try it.

1685
02:08:58,956 --> 02:09:00,415
We're not finished yet.

1686
02:09:05,379 --> 02:09:07,502
And then shawarma after.

1687
02:09:29,154 --> 02:09:31,397
If it's all the same to you,

1688
02:09:34,702 --> 02:09:36,362
I'll have that drink now.

1689
02:09:44,253 --> 02:09:46,293
<i>Despite the devastation
of what has been confirmed</i>

1690
02:09:46,422 --> 02:09:48,130
<i>as an extraterrestrial attack,</i>

1691
02:09:48,257 --> 02:09:49,799
<i>the extraordinary heroics</i>

1692
02:09:49,926 --> 02:09:51,884
<i>of the group known as the Avengers</i>

1693
02:09:52,012 --> 02:09:53,554
<i>has been to many a cause
not only for comfort,</i>

1694
02:09:53,680 --> 02:09:54,676
<i>but for celebration.</i>

1695
02:09:54,806 --> 02:09:57,214
<i>It's just really great knowing
they're out there.</i>

1696
02:09:57,351 --> 02:09:59,142
<i>That someone is watching over us.</i>

1697
02:09:59,269 --> 02:10:00,467
<i>I love you, Thor!</i>

1698
02:10:00,604 --> 02:10:02,312
<i>And then these guys were like...</i>

1699
02:10:02,439 --> 02:10:03,768
<i>And then the air goes...</i>

1700
02:10:03,899 --> 02:10:05,274
<i>And this green guy walks up
and he goes...</i>

1701
02:10:05,400 --> 02:10:06,432
<i>I don't know.</i>

1702
02:10:06,568 --> 02:10:09,024
<i>I don't exactly feel safer
with those things out there.</i>

1703
02:10:09,154 --> 02:10:12,240
<i>It just seems that there's
a lot they're not telling us.</i>

1704
02:10:12,367 --> 02:10:15,783
<i>Superheroes in New York?
Give me a break.</i>

1705
02:10:15,912 --> 02:10:17,821
<i>These so-called "heroes"</i>

1706
02:10:17,956 --> 02:10:19,236
<i>have to be held responsible</i>

1707
02:10:19,374 --> 02:10:21,532
<i>for the destruction done to this city.</i>

1708
02:10:21,668 --> 02:10:23,791
<i>This was their fight.
Where are they now?</i>

1709
02:10:23,920 --> 02:10:26,746
<i>Tough questions are being asked
about the Avengers themselves.</i>

1710
02:10:26,881 --> 02:10:27,877
<i>Their sudden appearance</i>

1711
02:10:28,007 --> 02:10:29,383
<i>and equally sudden disappearance...</i>

1712
02:10:29,509 --> 02:10:32,297
<i>What, this is all somehow their fault?</i>

1713
02:10:34,348 --> 02:10:37,515
<i>Captain America saved my life.</i>

1714
02:10:39,645 --> 02:10:43,144
<i>Wherever he is, and
wherever any of them are,</i>

1715
02:10:43,274 --> 02:10:44,768
<i>I would just...</i>

1716
02:10:45,568 --> 02:10:47,856
<i>I would want to say thank you.</i>

1717
02:10:50,322 --> 02:10:51,818
<i>Where are the Avengers?</i>

1718
02:10:51,950 --> 02:10:54,358
I'm not currently
tracking their whereabouts.

1719
02:10:54,494 --> 02:10:56,653
I'd say they've earned
a leave of absence.

1720
02:10:56,788 --> 02:10:58,366
<i>And the Tesseract?</i>

1721
02:10:58,498 --> 02:11:00,740
<i>The Tesseract is where it belongs.</i>

1722
02:11:01,168 --> 02:11:03,493
<i>Out of our reach.</i>

1723
02:11:03,628 --> 02:11:05,171
<i>That's not your call.</i>

1724
02:11:05,297 --> 02:11:06,328
I didn't make it.

1725
02:11:06,465 --> 02:11:08,706
I just didn't argue with the god that did.

1726
02:11:08,842 --> 02:11:10,633
<i>So, you let him take it</i>

1727
02:11:10,761 --> 02:11:12,386
<i>and the war criminal, Loki,</i>

1728
02:11:12,513 --> 02:11:14,221
<i>who should be
answering for his crime.</i>

1729
02:11:14,349 --> 02:11:16,922
<i>I think he will be.</i>

1730
02:11:30,406 --> 02:11:33,077
<i>I don't think you understand
what you've started,</i>

1731
02:11:33,202 --> 02:11:35,657
<i>letting the Avengers
loose on this world.</i>

1732
02:11:36,205 --> 02:11:37,201
<i>They're dangerous.</i>

1733
02:11:37,331 --> 02:11:40,996
<i>They surely are,
and the whole world knows it.</i>

1734
02:11:41,543 --> 02:11:44,117
Every world knows it.

1735
02:11:44,546 --> 02:11:46,622
<i>Was that the point of all this?</i>

1736
02:11:46,757 --> 02:11:48,500
<i>A statement?</i>

1737
02:11:51,220 --> 02:11:52,680
<i>A promise.</i>

1738
02:12:01,398 --> 02:12:02,940
<i>Sir, how does it work now?</i>

1739
02:12:04,067 --> 02:12:06,060
They've gone their separate ways.

1740
02:12:06,194 --> 02:12:09,112
Some, pretty extremely far.

1741
02:12:09,864 --> 02:12:11,774
If we get into a situation like this again,

1742
02:12:11,908 --> 02:12:13,451
what happens then?

1743
02:12:13,578 --> 02:12:14,573
They'll come back.

1744
02:12:16,080 --> 02:12:17,788
Are you really sure about that?

1745
02:12:17,915 --> 02:12:18,911
I am.

1746
02:12:20,543 --> 02:12:21,741
Why?

1747
02:12:22,795 --> 02:12:25,001
Because we'll need them to.

1748
02:15:16,603 --> 02:15:19,094
Humans.

1749
02:15:20,399 --> 02:15:24,728
They are not the cowering
wretches we were promised.

1750
02:15:25,696 --> 02:15:27,854
They stand.

1751
02:15:28,699 --> 02:15:35,153
They are unruly,
and therefore cannot be ruled.

1752
02:15:42,130 --> 02:15:45,000
To challenge them

1753
02:15:45,133 --> 02:15:48,833
is to court death.
